  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah and the Messengers of Ahaziah'
      title: Elijah and the Messengers of Ahaziah
      number: 1
      content: 'Moab rebelled against Israel after the death of Ahab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Ahaziah had fallen through the lattice in his upper room, which was
        in Samaria, and he was injured. So he sent messengers, and he said to them,
        \u201CGo, inquire of Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron, if I will survive this
        injury.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the angel of Yahweh spoke to Elijah the Tishbite, \u201CGet
        up, go up to meet the messengers of the king of Samaria and speak to them,
        \u2018Is it because there is no God in Israel that you are going to inquire
        of Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Therefore, thus says Yahweh, \u2018The bed upon which you have gone,
        you will not come down from it, but you shall surely die.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D
        So Elijah went. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When the messengers returned to him, he asked them, \u201CWhy have
        you returned?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then they said to him, \u201CA man came up to meet us, and he said
        to us, \u2018Go, return to the king who sent you and speak to him, \u201CThus
        says Yahweh, \u2018Is it because there is no God in Israel that you are sending
        to inquire of Baal-Zebub the god of Ekron? Therefore the bed upon which you
        have gone, you will not come down from it, for you will surely die.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then he spoke to them, \u201CWhat was the manner of the man who came
        up to meet you and spoke to you all these things?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They answered him, \u201CA hairy man with a leather belt girded around
        his waist.\u201D And he said, \u201CIt is Elijah the Tishbite.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Ahaziah sent to him the commander of fifty with his fifty men,
        and he went up to him while he was sitting on the top of the hill. He said
        to him, \u201CO man of God, the king says, \u2018Come down.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Elijah answered and said to the commander of the fifty, \u201CIf
        I am a man of God, let fire come down from heaven and consume you and your
        fifty!\u201D Then fire came down from heaven and consumed him and his fifty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So he again sent another commander of fifty and his fifty men. He
        answered and said to him, \u201CO man of God, thus says the king, \u2018Come
        down quickly!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Elijah answered and said to them, \u201CIf I am a man of God,
        then let fire come down from heaven and consume you and your fifty!\u201D
        Then the fire of God came down from heaven and consumed him and his fifty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So he again sent a third time a commander of fifty and his fifty,
        and the commander of the third fifty went up and came and knelt down on his
        knees before Elijah and entreated him. He said to him, \u201CO man of God,
        please let my life and the lives of your servants, these fifty, be precious
        in your eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Behold, fire from heaven came down and consumed the first two commanders
        of fifty and their fifties, so then let my life be precious in your eyes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the angel of Yahweh spoke to Elijah, \u201CGo down with him.
        Do not be afraid because of him.\u201D So he got up and went down with him
        to the king, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Epitaph for Ahaziah'
      title: Epitaph for Ahaziah
      number: 16
      content: "and he said to him, \u201CThus says Yahweh, \u2018Because you have
        sent messengers to inquire of Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron\u2014is it because
        there is no God in Israel from whom to inquire his word?\u2014therefore the
        bed upon which you went, you shall not come down from it, for you shall surely
        die.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So he died, according to the word of Yahweh which Elijah had spoken,
        and Joram became king in his place in the second year of Joram the son of
        Jehoshaphat, the king of Judah, because he had no son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Ahaziah which he did, are they not written
        in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah Taken Away from Elisha'
      title: Elijah Taken Away from Elisha
      number: 1
      content: 'When Yahweh was about to take Elijah up in the storm to heaven, Elijah
        and Elisha went from Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Elijah said to Elisha, \u201CPlease stay here, for Yahweh has sent
        me up to Bethel.\u201D Elisha said, \u201CAs Yahweh lives and as your soul
        lives, I will certainly not leave you!\u201D So they went down to Bethel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the sons of the prophets who were in Bethel came out to Elisha,
        and they said to him, \u201CDo you know that Yahweh is going to take your
        master from you today?\u201D He said, \u201CI also know; be quiet!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Elijah said to him, \u201CElisha, please stay here because Yahweh
        has sent me to Jericho.\u201D And he said, \u201CAs Yahweh lives and as your
        soul lives, I will certainly not leave you!\u201D So they came to Jericho. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the sons of the prophets who were in Jericho came near to Elisha,
        and they said to him, \u201CDo you know that Yahweh is going to take your
        master from you today?\u201D He said, \u201CI also know; be quiet!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Elijah said to him, \u201CPlease stay here, because Yahweh has
        sent me to the Jordan.\u201D He said, \u201CAs Yahweh lives and as your soul
        lives, I will certainly not leave you!\u201D So the two of them went on. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then fifty men from the sons of the prophets went and stood opposite
        them at a distance while the two of them stood by the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Elijah took his cloak, rolled it up, and struck the water. It divided
        in two, and the two of them crossed over on dry land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "After they crossed over, Elijah said to Elisha, \u201CAsk what I
        may do for you before I am taken away from you.\u201D Then Elisha said, \u201CPlease
        let there come to me a double portion of your spirit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He said, \u201CWhat you ask is difficult. If you see me being taken
        from you, it will be so for you, but if not, it will not happen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then they were walking, talking as they went. Suddenly a fiery chariot
        with horses of fire appeared and separated between the two of them. Elijah
        went up in the storm to the heavens '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "while Elisha was watching and crying out, \u201CMy father, my father;
        the chariot of Israel and its horsemen!\u201D But he could not see him any
        longer, and he grasped his clothes and tore them in two pieces. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then he picked up Elijah\u2019s cloak that had fallen off of him,
        and he returned and stood on the bank of the Jordan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Elisha Begins His Ministry'
      title: Elisha Begins His Ministry
      number: 14
      content: "He took Elijah\u2019s cloak that had fallen from upon him and struck
        the water. Then he said, \u201CWhere is Yahweh, the God of Elijah?\u201D
        So he also struck the water, and it divided in two, and Elisha crossed over. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When the sons of the prophets who were at Jericho saw him from the
        other side, they declared, \u201CThe spirit of Elijah rests upon Elisha,\u201D
        and they came to meet him and bowed down to him to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then they said to him, \u201CLook, there are with your servants fifty
        able men. Please let them go and look for your master, lest the Spirit of
        Yahweh has lifted him up and thrown him on one of the mountains or into one
        of the valleys,\u201D but he said, \u201CYou must not send them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But they urged him until embarrassing him, so he said, \u201CSend
        them.\u201D So they sent fifty men, and they looked for three days, but they
        could not find him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then they returned to him while he was staying in Jericho. He said
        to them, \u201CDid I not tell you not to go?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The men of the city said to Elisha, \u201CPlease now, the location
        of the city is good, as my master can see, but the water is bad and the land
        unproductive.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So he said, \u201CBring me a new bowl and put salt in it.\u201D So
        they brought it to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then he went out to the spring of waters and threw the salt into
        it there and said, \u201CThus says Yahweh, \u2018I hereby purify these waters;
        let there be no longer any death or unproductiveness from it.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the waters were purified until this very day according to the
        word of Elisha that he spoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then he went up from there to Bethel; as he was going up along the
        way, young boys came out from the city and mocked at him and said to him,
        \u201CGo up, baldhead; go up, baldhead!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When he turned around and saw them, he cursed them in the name of
        Yahweh. Then two bears came out of the forest and mauled forty-two boys among
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then he went from there to Mount Carmel and from there he returned
        to Samaria. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joram Meets Moab in Battle'
      title: Joram Meets Moab in Battle
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Joram the son of Ahab had become king over Israel in Samaria
        in the eighteenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah. He reigned twelve years '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and did evil in the eyes of Yahweh, yet not as his father or his
        mother, as he removed the stone pillars of Baal that his father had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But he did cling to the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat who caused
        Israel to sin, and he did not depart from it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Mesha king of Moab was a sheep breeder, and he used to deliver
        to the king of Israel a hundred thousand male lambs and a hundred thousand
        wool rams. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'It happened that when Ahab died, Mesha king of Moab rebelled against
        the king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So King Joram went out on that day from Samaria, and he mustered
        all of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He went and sent a message to Jehoshaphat king of Judah, saying,
        \u201CThe king of Moab has rebelled against me. Will you go with me against
        Moab for the battle?\u201D And he said, \u201CI will go up. I am like you;
        my people are like your people; my horses are like your horses.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he said, \u201CWhich way shall we go up?\u201D And he answered,
        \u201CBy way of the wilderness of Edom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the king of Israel and the king of Judah and the king of Edom
        went around, a way of seven days, but there was no water for the army or
        for the animals which were with them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the king of Israel said, \u201CAha, Yahweh has called for these
        three kings to give them into the hand of Moab.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Jehoshaphat asked, \u201CIs there no prophet of Yahweh here
        that we might inquire guidance from Yahweh?\u201D One of the servants of
        the king of Israel answered and said, \u201CElisha the son of Shaphat is
        here, who poured water on the hands of Elijah.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Jehoshaphat said, \u201CThe word of Yahweh is with him.\u201D So
        the king of Israel, Jehoshaphat, and the king of Edom went down to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Elisha said to the king of Israel, \u201CWhat do we have in
        common? Go to the prophets of your father and to the prophets of your mother.\u201D
        Then the king of Israel said to him, \u201CNo, for Yahweh has called for
        these three kings to give them into the hand of Moab.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Elisha said, \u201CAs Yahweh of hosts lives, before whom I stand,
        surely if I was not regarding the face of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, I would
        have not looked at you nor even glanced at you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But now, bring me a musician.\u201D It happened that at the moment
        the musician played, the hand of Yahweh came upon him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He said, \u201CThus says Yahweh, \u2018Make this wadi full of cisterns,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "for thus says Yahweh, \u2018You will see neither wind nor rain, yet
        this wadi will be full of water; and you and all of your livestock and your
        animals shall drink.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And since this is too trivial in the eyes of Yahweh, he will also
        give Moab into your hand, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and you shall defeat every fortified city, every choice city, and
        you shall fell every good tree. All of the springs of water you shall stop
        up, and every tract of good land you shall ruin with the stones.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'It happened in the morning about the time of the morning offering,
        that water was suddenly coming from the direction of Edom and the land was
        filled with water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now all of Moab had heard that the kings had come up to fight against
        them, and all who were fighting age and up were called up, and they stood
        at the border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When they arose early in the morning, the sun shone on the waters,
        and Moab saw the waters from the opposite side as red as blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then they said, \u201CThis is blood! Certainly the kings have fought
        one another, and each has killed his neighbor. Now, to the war booty, O Moab!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But when they came to the camp of Israel, Israel stood up and killed
        Moab, so that they fled from before them. They came at her and defeated Moab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The cities they tore down, on every good tract of land they threw
        stones until it was filled up, every spring of water they stopped up, and
        every good tree they felled. They let the stone walls at Kir Hareseth remain,
        but the slingers surrounded and attacked it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When the king of Moab saw that the battle was too heavy for him,
        he took with him seven hundred men who drew the sword to break through to
        the king of Edom, but they were not able. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He took his firstborn son who was to become king in his place and
        offered him as a burnt offering on the wall. Great wrath came upon Israel,
        and they withdrew from him and returned to the land. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elisha Answers a Widow\u2019s Request"
      title: "Elisha Answers a Widow\u2019s Request"
      number: 1
      content: "A certain woman from the wives of the sons of the prophets cried
        out to Elisha, saying, \u201CYour servant my husband is dead. Now you know
        that your servant was a fearer of Yahweh, but the creditor came to take two
        of my children for himself as slaves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Elisha asked her, \u201CWhat shall I do for you? Tell me, what do
        you have in the house?\u201D Then she said, \u201CYour servant has nothing
        in the house except a jar of olive oil.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then he said to her, \u201CGo, ask for yourself some containers from
        the streets, from all your neighbors. You must collect as many empty containers
        as you can!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You must also go and shut the door behind you and your children,
        and you must pour out oil into all of these containers and set the filled
        ones aside.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So she went from him, and she shut the door behind her and her children.
        They were bringing containers to her, and she kept pouring. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "It happened that when the containers were full, she said to her son,
        \u201CBring near me another container,\u201D but he said to her, \u201CThere
        is not another container.\u201D Then the olive oil stopped flowing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Elisha at Shunem'
      title: Elisha at Shunem
      number: 7
      content: "So she came and told the man of God, and he said, \u201CGo, sell
        the olive oil and repay your debt. You and your sons can live on what is
        left over.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'It happened one day that Elisha passed through to Shunem where there
        was a wealthy woman, and she urged him to eat bread; so it happened each
        time he passed through, he would stop there to eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "She said to her husband, \u201CPlease now, I know that he is a holy
        man of God who is passing our way regularly; "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'let us make a small enclosed room upstairs and put a bed, table,
        chair, and lampstand there for him, so that when he comes to us, he can turn
        and stay there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'One day it happened that he came there and went to the upper room
        and lay down there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He said to Gehazi his servant, \u201CCall to this Shunammite,\u201D
        so he called to her, and she stood before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He said to him, \u201CPlease say to her, \u2018Look, you took all
        this trouble, showing care for us; what is there for me to do for you? To
        speak for you to the king or to the commander of the army?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D
        She said, \u201CI am living among my people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he said, \u201CWhat may be done for her?\u201D Gehazi said,
        \u201CWell, she has no son, and her husband is old.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he said, \u201CCall for her,\u201D so he called for her and she
        stood in the doorway. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he said, \u201CAt this time next spring, you will be embracing
        a son.\u201D She said, \u201CNo, my lord, O man of God! You must not tell
        a lie to your servant!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Elisha Restores the Shunammite\u2019s Son"
      title: "Elisha Restores the Shunammite\u2019s Son"
      number: 17
      content: 'But the woman conceived, and she bore a son in the spring, which
        Elisha had promised to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The child grew older, and it happened one day that he went out to
        his father and to the reapers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he said to his father, \u201CMy head, my head!\u201D So he said
        to the servant, \u201CCarry him to his mother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So they carried him and brought him to his mother; he sat on her
        lap until noon and then died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'She went up, laid him on the bed of the man of God, closed the door,
        and went out behind it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "She called to her husband and said, \u201CPlease send one of the
        servants and one of the female donkeys for me, so that I can go quickly up
        to the man of God and return.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhy are you going to him today? It is neither
        the new moon nor the Sabbath!\u201D And she said, \u201CPeace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "She saddled the female donkey, and she said to her servant, \u201CDrive
        along and go; you must not hold me back from riding, unless I tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So she went and came to the man of God by Mount Carmel. It happened
        when the man of God saw her at a distance, he said to Gehazi his servant,
        \u201CThere is this Shunammite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Now, please run to meet her and ask her, \u2018Is it peace for you?
        Is it peace for your husband? Is it peace for the boy?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D
        She said, \u201CPeace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So she came to the man of God at the mountain, and she caught hold
        of his feet. Then Gehazi came near to push her away, but the man of God said,
        \u201CLet her alone, for her soul is bitter, and Yahweh has hidden it from
        me and has not told me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then she said, \u201CDid I ask for a son from my lord? Did I not
        say that you must not mislead me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then he said to Gehazi, \u201CGird up your loins and take my staff
        in your hand and go. If you meet anyone, you must not greet them; if anyone
        greets you, you must not answer them. You must put my staff on the face of
        the boy.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then the mother of the boy said, \u201CAs Yahweh lives and as your
        soul lives, I will surely not leave you.\u201D So he got up and went after
        her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Gehazi crossed over before them, and he put the staff on the face
        of the boy; but there was no sound, and there was no sign of life, so he
        returned to meet him. He told him, saying, \u201CThe boy did not wake up.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When Elisha came to the house, here was the boy dead, lying on his
        bed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He went and closed the door behind the two of them and prayed to
        Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then he went up and lay upon the child and put his mouth on his mouth,
        his eyes on his eyes, and his palms on his palms. As he bent down over him,
        the flesh of the boy became warm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'He returned and went to and fro in the house one time, then he went
        up and bent over him. Then the boy sneezed seven times and opened his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Elisha called to Gehazi and said, \u201CCall this Shunammite.\u201D
        So he called her and she came to him; then he said, \u201CPick up your son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: Elisha Secures the Food'
      title: Elisha Secures the Food
      number: 37
      content: 'She came and fell at his feet and bowed down to the ground; then
        she picked up her son and went out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So Elisha returned to Gilgal. Now the famine was in the land, and
        the sons of the prophets were sitting before him. He said to his servant,
        put on the large pot and cook a stew for the sons of the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'One went out to the field to gather herbs, and he found a wild vine
        and gathered wild gourds from it and filled his cloak. Then he came and cut
        them into the pot of stew, but they did not know what they were. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "They served the men to eat, but when they ate from the stew, they
        cried out and said, \u201CThere is death in the pot, O man of God!\u201D
        They were not able to eat it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Then he said, \u201CBring some flour,\u201D and he threw it into
        the pot. He then said, \u201CServe the people and let them eat.\u201D There
        was nothing harmful in the pot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "A man came from Baal-Shalishah and brought food to the man of God:
        firstfruits and twenty loaves of barley bread, with ripe grain in his sack.
        He said, \u201CGive it to the people and let them eat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Then his servant said, \u201CHow can I set this before a hundred
        men?\u201D He said, \u201CGive it to the people and let them eat, for thus
        Yahweh says, \u2018They shall eat and have some left over.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'So he set it before them, and they ate and had some left over, according
        to the word of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Healing of Naaman the Syrian'
      title: The Healing of Naaman the Syrian
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Naaman was the commander of the army of the king of Aram. He
        was a great man before his master and highly regarded, for by him Yahweh
        had given victory to Aram. Now the man was a mighty warrior, but he was afflicted
        with a skin disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When the Arameans went on a raid, they brought back a young girl
        from the land of Israel, and she came into the service of the wife of Naaman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "She said to her mistress, \u201CIf only my lord would come before
        the prophet who is in Samaria; then he would cure his skin disease.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He came and told his master, saying, \u201CThus and so the girl who
        is from the land of Israel said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So the king of Aram said, \u201CGo, I will send a letter to the king
        of Israel.\u201D He went and took with him ten talents of silver, six thousand
        shekels of gold, and ten sets of clothing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So he brought the letter of the king to Israel, saying, \u201CNow,
        when this letter comes to you, I have just sent Naaman my servant to you
        that you may cure him from his skin disease.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "It happened that when the king of Israel read the letter, he tore
        his clothes and said, \u201CAm I God to cause death or to give life? This
        man is sending a man to me to cure his disease. Indeed! But know and see
        that he seeks an opportunity against me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "It happened that as soon as Elisha the man of God heard that the
        king of Israel had torn his clothes, he sent to the king, saying, \u201CWhy
        did you tear your clothes? Please may he come to me, that he might know that
        there is a prophet in Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Naaman came with his horses and his chariots, and he stopped
        at the doorway of the house of Elisha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Elisha sent a messenger to him, saying, \u201CGo, you must wash seven
        times in the Jordan, then your flesh shall return to you, and you shall be
        clean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Naaman became angry and he went and said, \u201CLook, I said
        to myself, \u2018Surely he will come out, stand, call upon the name of Yahweh
        his God, and wave his hands over the spot; then he would take away the skin
        disease.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Are not the Abana and the Pharpar, the rivers of Damascus, better
        than all of the waters of Israel? Could I not wash in them that I may be
        clean?\u201D Then he turned and left in anger. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But his servants came near and spoke to him and said, \u201CMy father,
        if the prophet had spoken a difficult thing to you to do, would you not have
        done it? Why not even when he says to you, \u2018Wash and you shall be clean\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Elisha\u2019s Greedy Servant Gehazi"
      title: "Elisha\u2019s Greedy Servant Gehazi"
      number: 14
      content: 'So he went down and plunged into the Jordan seven times, according
        to the word of the man of God, and his flesh returned as the flesh of a small
        boy, and he was clean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When he returned to the man of God, he and all of his army, he came
        and stood before him and said, \u201CPlease now, I know that there is no
        God in all of the world except in Israel. So then, please take a gift from
        your servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he said, \u201CAs Yahweh lives, before whom I stand, I surely
        will not take it.\u201D Still he urged him to take it, but he refused. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Naaman said, \u201CIf not, then please let a load of soil on
        a pair of mules be given to your servants, for your servant will never again
        bring a burnt offering and sacrifice to other gods, but only to Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "As far as this matter, may Yahweh pardon your servant when my master
        goes into the house of Rimmon to worship there, and he is leaning himself
        on my arm, that I also bow down in the house of Rimmon: when I bow down in
        the house of Rimmon, may Yahweh please pardon your servant in this matter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He said to him, \u201CGo in peace,\u201D so he went from him a short
        distance.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Gehazi the servant of Elisha, the man of God, thought, \u201CLook,
        my master has refrained from taking what this Aramean Naaman brought from
        his hand. As Yahweh lives, I will certainly run after him, and I will accept
        something from him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So Gehazi pursued after Naaman. When Naaman saw someone running after
        him, he jumped off his chariot to meet him and asked him, \u201CIs it peace?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He said, \u201CPeace. My master has sent me saying, \u2018Look, just
        now two servants from the hill country of Ephraim came to me, from the sons
        of the prophets. Please give them a talent of silver and two sets of clothing.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Naaman said, \u201CBe prepared to accept two talents.\u201D
        So he urged him and tied up two talents of silver in two bags, with two sets
        of clothing and gave it to two of his servants and they carried it before
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When he came to the citadel, he took them from their hand and put
        them in the house, then sent away the men so that they went. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "When he went and stood by his master, Elisha asked him, \u201CFrom
        where have you come, Gehazi?\u201D And he said, \u201CYour servant has not
        gone anywhere.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then he said to him, \u201CDid not my heart go with you as the man
        turned from on his chariot to meet you? Is it time to take silver, clothes,
        olive orchards, vineyards, sheep, oxen, male slaves, and female slaves? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The skin disease of Naaman shall cling to you and to your offspring
        forever.\u201D Then he went out from before him having a skin disease like
        the snow. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elisha Recovers a Lost Axe Head'
      title: Elisha Recovers a Lost Axe Head
      number: 1
      content: "Then the sons of the prophets said to Elisha, \u201CPlease look;
        the place where we are living before you is too cramped for us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Let us please go to the Jordan and each bring from there one log
        that we might make a place there for us to live.\u201D Then he said, \u201CDo
        so.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then a certain one said, \u201CPlease be prepared and go with your
        servants,\u201D and he said, \u201CI will go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He went with them, and they went to the Jordan, and they cut down
        the trees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "It happened as the one was felling the log, that the iron ax fell
        into the water. He called out and said, \u201COh, no! My master, it was borrowed!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the man of God said, \u201CWhere did it fall?\u201D So he showed
        him the place, and then he cut off a stick and threw it there and made the
        iron ax float. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Arameans Plot to Take Elisha'
      title: Arameans Plot to Take Elisha
      number: 7
      content: "Then he said, \u201CPick it up for yourself,\u201D so he stretched
        out his hand and took it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The king of Aram was fighting with Israel, so he consulted with his
        officers, saying, \u201CMy camp is at such and such a place.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the man of God sent to the king of Israel, saying, \u201CTake
        care while crossing over to this place, because the Arameans are descending
        there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the king of Israel sent to the place which the man of God said
        to him and warned him, so he was on guard there continually.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the heart of the king of Aram was stormy because of this matter,
        so he called his servants and said to them, \u201CCan you not tell me who
        among us sides with the king of Israel?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then one of his servants said, \u201CNo, my lord the king, but Elisha
        the prophet who is in Israel tells the king of Israel things which you speak
        in your own bedchamber.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then he said, \u201CGo and see where he is so that I can send and
        capture him.\u201D Then he was told to him, \u201CLook, he is in Dothan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So he sent horses, chariots, and an oppressing army there. They arrived
        at night and surrounded the town. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The attendant of the man of God arose early and went out, and look,
        the army was surrounding the city with horses and chariots. His servant said
        to him, \u201COh no, my master! What shall we do?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he said, \u201CDon\u2019t be afraid, for more are with us than
        are with them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Elisha prayed and said, \u201CO Yahweh, please open his eyes
        that he may see,\u201D and Yahweh opened the eyes of the servant, and he
        saw, and look, the mountain was full of horses and chariots of fire all around
        Elisha. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "They came down to him, and Elisha prayed to Yahweh and said, \u201CPlease
        strike this people with blindness,\u201D so he struck them with blindness
        as Elisha had spoken.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Elisha said to them, \u201CThis is not the way and this is not
        the city. Come after me, and I will bring you to the man whom you seek.\u201D
        Then he brought them to Samaria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "It happened at the moment they came to Samaria, Elisha said, \u201CO
        Yahweh, open the eyes of these that they may see,\u201D so Yahweh opened
        their eyes, and they saw, and look, the middle of Samaria! "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the king of Israel said to Elisha when he saw them, \u201CShall
        I kill them? Shall I kill, my father?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And he said, \u201CYou shall not kill. Would you kill those whom
        you took captive with the sword or with the bow? Put food and water before
        them that they may eat and drink and then go to their master.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Besieged Samaria Resorts to Cannibalism'
      title: Besieged Samaria Resorts to Cannibalism
      number: 23
      content: 'So he made a great feast for them, and they ate and drank; then he
        sent them, and they went to their master. And the bands of the Arameans did
        not come again into the land of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'It happened after this that Ben-Hadad king of Aram assembled all
        of his army and marched up and laid siege against Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'There was a great famine in Samaria, and behold, a siege was against
        it, until the head of a donkey went for eighty shekels of silver, and one
        fourth of the measure of the dung of doves went for five shekels of silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "It happened that the king of Israel was crossing over on the wall,
        and a woman called out to him, saying, \u201CHelp, my lord the king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "He said, \u201CNo, let Yahweh help you. How can I save you? From
        the threshing floor or from the wine press?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The king said to her, \u201CWhat is the problem?\u201D Then the woman
        said, \u201CThis woman said to me, \u2018Give me your son, and let us eat
        him today, then tomorrow we will eat my son.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So we cooked my son and ate him, and I said to her the next day,
        \u2018Give your son that we may eat him.\u2019 But she had hidden her son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'It happened that when the king heard the words of the woman, he tore
        his clothes. Now he had been walking on the wall, and the people saw, and
        behold, sackcloth was over his flesh underneath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he said, \u201CMay God do to me and thus may he add, if the
        head of Elisha the son of Shaphat remains on him today!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Now Elisha was sitting in his house and the elders were sitting with
        him, and the king dispatched a man from before him, but before the messenger
        came to him, he said to the elders, \u201CDid you see that this son of a
        murderer has sent to remove my head? Look, when the messenger comes, close
        the door; and you must hold the door closed against him. Is not the sound
        of the feet of his master behind him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "While he was still speaking with them, suddenly the messenger was
        coming down to him, and he said, \u201CLook this trouble is from Yahweh.
        Why should I wait for Yahweh any longer?\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elisha Prophesies Hope for Relief'
      title: Elisha Prophesies Hope for Relief
      number: 1
      content: "Elisha said, \u201CHear the word of Yahweh: \u2018Thus says Yahweh,
        \u201CAt this time tomorrow a seah of wheat bread flour will sell for a shekel,
        and two seahs of barley for a shekel in the gate of Samaria.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Four Lepers Report the Departure of the Arameans'
      title: Four Lepers Report the Departure of the Arameans
      number: 2
      content: "Then the officer on whom the king relied answered the man of God
        and said, \u201CLook, even if Yahweh is making windows in heaven, could this
        thing happen?\u201D And he said, \u201CLook, you will be seeing it with your
        eyes, but you shall not eat from it there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now four men who had a skin disease were at the entrance of the gate,
        and they said to each other, \u201CWhy are we sitting here until we die? "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "If we say, \u2018Let us go into the city,\u2019 the famine is in
        the city, and we shall die there; but if we sit here, we shall die. So then,
        come, let us fall into the camp of the Arameans. If they let us live, we
        shall live; but if they kill us, then we shall die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So they got up at dusk to go to the camp of the Arameans. They went
        up to the edge of the camp of the Arameans, and look, there was no man there! '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now the Lord had caused the camp of the Arameans to hear the sound
        of chariots, the sound of horses, and the sound of a great army. So they
        said to one another, \u201CLook, the king of Israel has hired the kings of
        the Hittites and the kings of Egypt to come against us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So they got up and fled at dusk and left their tents, their horses,
        their donkeys, and the camp as it was, and they fled for their lives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When these who had the skin disease came to the edge of the camp,
        they went into a certain tent and they ate, drank, and took from there silver
        and gold and clothes. Then they went and hid them, then returned and came
        to another tent, and they took from there and went and hid them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then they said to one another, \u201CWe are not doing right. This
        day is a day of good news! If we are silent and wait until the light of morning,
        they will find us and we will be punished. So then, come, let us go and tell
        the house of the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When they came, they called to the gatekeepers of the city and told
        them, saying, \u201CWe came to the camp of the Arameans, and behold, there
        was no man or the voice of a man there! Only the horses and the donkeys were
        tied up, and the tents were left as they were.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the gatekeepers called and told it inside the house of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The king got up in the night and said to his servants, \u201CPlease
        let me tell you what the Arameans have done to us. The Arameans know that
        we are hungry, so they went out from the camp to hide in the field, saying,
        \u2018When they go out from the city, we shall seize them alive and go into
        the city.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then one of his servants replied and said, \u201CPlease let them
        take five of the remaining horses which remain in the city; behold, they
        are like all of the multitude of Israel that remain in it; they are like
        all the multitude of Israel who have perished. Let us send and see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So he took two charioteer horsemen, and the king sent after the camp
        of the Arameans, saying, \u201CGo, find out,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Prophecy Fulfilled'
      title: Prophecy Fulfilled
      number: 15
      content: 'and they went after them to the Jordan. Look, all of the way was
        littered with clothes and equipment which the Arameans had thrown away in
        their haste. Then the messengers returned and told the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So the people went out and plundered the camp of the Arameans. A
        seah of wheat flour went for a shekel and two seahs of barley went for a
        shekel according to the word of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the king appointed the officer he was depending on over the
        gate, but the people trampled him and he died, according to that which the
        man of God had said which he spoke when the king came down to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "It happened as the man of God spoke to the king, saying, \u201CTwo
        seahs of barley shall be sold for a shekel and a seah of wheat flour for
        a shekel at this time tomorrow in the gate of Samaria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the officer had replied to the man of God and said, \u201CLook,
        even if Yahweh is opening the windows in heaven, could this thing happen?\u201D
        And he had said, \u201CLook you are about to see it with your eyes, but you
        will not eat from it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So it had happened to him; the people trampled him in the gate and
        he died. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joram Restores the Shunammite\u2019s Land"
      title: "Joram Restores the Shunammite\u2019s Land"
      number: 1
      content: "Elisha spoke to the woman whose son he had restored to life, saying,
        \u201CGet up and go, you and your household, and dwell as an alien wherever
        you can, for Yahweh has called for a famine, and it will come to the land
        for seven years.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the woman got up and did according to the word of the man of God.
        She and her household went and dwelt as an alien in the land of the Philistines
        for seven years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It happened at the end of seven years that the woman returned from
        the land of the Philistines and went out to appeal to the king for her household
        and for her properties.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now the king was speaking to Gehazi the servant of the man of God,
        saying, \u201CPlease tell me all of the great things which Elisha has done.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "It happened that as he was telling the king how he had restored the
        dead to life, suddenly the woman whose son he had restored to life was crying
        out to the king about her household and about her field. Then Gehazi said,
        \u201CMy lord the king, this is the woman and this is her son whom Elisha
        restored to life!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the king asked the woman, and she told him. So the king appointed
        for her a certain court official, saying, \u201CRestore all that is hers
        and all the yield of the field from the day she left the land up to now.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Elisha came to Damascus. Now Ben-Hadad king of Aram was ill, and
        he was told, \u201CThe man of God has come up here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the king said to Hazael, \u201CTake a gift in your hand and
        go meet the man of God. Inquire of Yahweh from him, saying, \u2018Shall I
        recover from this illness?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Hazael went to meet him and took a gift in his hand of all of
        the good things of Damascus, a load on each of forty camels, and he came
        and stood before him. Then he said, \u201CYour son Ben-Hadad king of Aram
        has sent me to you, saying, \u2018Shall I recover from this illness?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Elisha said to him, \u201CGo; say to him, \u2018You shall certainly
        recover,\u2019 but Yahweh has shown me that he certainly will die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the man fixed his gaze and stared at him until he was ashamed
        and the man of God cried. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Hazael asked, \u201CWhy is my lord crying?\u201D He said, \u201CBecause
        I know what evil you will do to the Israelites. You will set their fortifications
        on fire, and you will kill their young men with the sword. Their little ones
        you will dash to pieces, and their pregnant women you will rip open!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Hazael said, \u201CBut how could your servant, who is like a
        dog, do this great thing?\u201D Elisha said, \u201CYahweh has shown me that
        you are to be king over Aram.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So he departed from Elisha and came to his master. He asked him,
        \u201CWhat did Elisha say to you.\u201D So he said, \u201CHe said to me that
        you will certainly recover.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Joram Reigns in Judah'
      title: Joram Reigns in Judah
      number: 15
      content: 'On the next day, he took the bed cover, dipped it in the water, and
        spread it over his face so that he died. Then Hazael became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now in the fifth year of Joram son of Ahab, king of Israel, and Jehoshaphat
        king of Judah, Joram son of Jehoshaphat became the king of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He was thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned eight
        years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He walked in the way of the kings of Israel as the house of Ahab
        had done, for the daughter of Ahab became his wife, and he did evil in the
        eyes of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Yet Yahweh was not willing to destroy Judah, for the sake of David
        his servant, as he had promised to give him a lamp for his sons always. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In his days, Edom rebelled against the rule of Judah, and they set
        up a king over them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So Joram crossed over to Zair and all the chariots with him. It happened
        that he arose by night and attacked Edom who had surrounded him and the commanders
        of the chariots; but the army fled to their tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Edom has rebelled against the rule of Judah until this day; then
        Libnah also rebelled at that time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Joram and all that he did, are they
        not written in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Ahaziah Succeeds Joram in Judah'
      title: Ahaziah Succeeds Joram in Judah
      number: 24
      content: 'So Joram slept with his ancestors, and he was buried with his ancestors
        in the city of David, and Ahaziah his son became king in place of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'In the twelfth year of Joram the son of Ahab, king of Israel, Ahaziah
        the son of Joram became king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Ahaziah was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned
        one year in Jerusalem. The name of his mother was Athaliah daughter of Omri,
        king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He walked in the way of the house of Ahab and did evil in the eyes
        of Yahweh, as the house of Ahab; for he was the son-in-law of the house of
        Ahab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He went with Joram the son of Ahab for the battle against Hazael
        king of Aram at Ramoth-Gilead, and the Arameans wounded Joram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Joram the king returned to Jezreel to heal from the wounds which
        the Arameans had inflicted at Ramah when Hazael king of Aram fought him.
        Ahaziah the son of Joram, king of Judah, went down to see Joram the son of
        Ahab in Jezreel, for he was ill. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehu Anointed Prophetically to Rule in Place of Joram of Israel'
      title: Jehu Anointed Prophetically to Rule in Place of Joram of Israel
      number: 1
      content: "Now Elisha the prophet called for one of the sons of the prophets,
        and he said to him, \u201CGird your loins, and take this flask of olive oil
        in your hand, and go to Ramoth-Gilead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Go there and look there for Jehu the son of Jehoshaphat the son of
        Nimshi. Go, for you must cause him to arise from among his brothers, and
        you must bring him into an inner room.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You must take the flask of olive oil and pour it out on his head.
        You must say, \u2018Thus says Yahweh, \u201CI hereby anoint you as king over
        Israel.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 Then you must open the door and flee; do not linger!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the young man, servant of the prophet, went to Ramoth-Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He came, and look, the commanders of the army were sitting there.
        He said, \u201CI have a word for you, O commander!\u201D Jehu said, \u201CFor
        whom? For all of us?\u201D And he said, \u201CFor you, O commander!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He got up and went to the house, and poured the olive oil on his
        head and said to him, \u201CThus says Yahweh, the God of Israel: \u2018I
        hereby anoint you as king over the people of Yahweh, over Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You will destroy the house of Ahab your master, and you will avenge
        the blood of my servants the prophets and the blood of all of the servants
        of Yahweh, from the hand of Jezebel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'All of the house of Ahab will perish, and I shall cut off all males
        from Ahab, both bond and free. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will make the house of Ahab like the house of Jeroboam the son
        of Nebat and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Jehu Assassinates Joram'
      title: Jehu Assassinates Joram
      number: 10
      content: "The dogs will eat Jezebel in the territory of Jezreel, and there
        shall not be anyone to bury her.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D Then he opened the door
        and fled. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Jehu came out to the officers of his master, and they said to
        him, \u201CPeace? Why did this madman come to you?\u201D And he said to them,
        \u201CYou know the man and his foolish talk.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then they said, \u201CLiar. Please tell us.\u201D He said, \u201CThus
        and so he said to me, saying, \u2018Thus says Yahweh, \u201CI hereby anoint
        you as king over Israel.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So they hastened each one to take his cloak, and they spread them
        under him on the bare steps, blew on the trumpet, and said, \u201CJehu is
        king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Jehu the son of Jehoshaphat the son of Nimshi conspired against
        Joram. Now Joram was keeping guard in Ramoth-Gilead, he and all of Israel,
        because of the threat of Hazael king of Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But Joram the king had returned to heal in Jezreel from the wound
        which the Arameans had inflicted on him when he fought with Hazael king of
        Aram. Jehu said, \u201CIf this is what you want, do not let him go out as
        a fugitive from the city to go to make it known in Jezreel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Jehu mounted his chariot and went to Jezreel, for Joram was lying
        there, and Ahaziah king of Judah had gone down to visit Joram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now the watchman was standing on the tower in Jezreel, and he saw
        the company of Jehu when he came, and he said, \u201CI see a company.\u201D
        Joram said, \u201CTake a horseman and send him to meet them.\u201D And he
        said, \u201CIs it peace?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So the rider of the horse went out to meet him, and he said, \u201CThus
        the king asks, \u2018Is it peace?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D Then Jehu said, \u201CWhat
        do you have to do with peace? Turn after me.\u201D Then the watchman reported,
        saying, \u201CThe messenger went up to them, but he did not return.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he sent out a second horseman, and he came to them and said,
        \u201CThus the king asks, \u2018Is it peace?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D Then Jehu
        said, \u201CWhat do you have to do with peace? Turn after me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So the sentinel reported, saying, \u201CHe went up to them, but he
        did not return, and the driving is like the driving of Jehu the son of Nimshi,
        for he drives with madness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Joram said, \u201CGet ready,\u201D so he got his chariot ready.
        Joram king of Israel went out, and Ahaziah king of Judah, each with his chariot.
        They went out to meet Jehu, and they found him at the tract of land of Naboth
        the Jezreelite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "When Joram saw Jehu, he asked, \u201CIs it peace?\u201D And he said,
        \u201CWhat peace is there while the prostitutions of your mother Jezebel
        and her sorceries are numerous?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Joram turned his chariot and fled and said to Ahaziah, \u201CIt\u2019s
        treason, Ahaziah!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then Jehu drew his bow and shot Joram between his shoulders so that
        the arrow went out from his heart, and he slumped down in his chariot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "He said to Bidkar his third servant, \u201CLift him out and throw
        him on the plot of the field of Naboth the Jezreelite, for remember, you
        and I were with the pair of chariots behind Ahab his father when Yahweh pronounced
        this oracle against him: "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Jehu Orders the Assassination of Ahaziah'
      title: Jehu Orders the Assassination of Ahaziah
      number: 26
      content: "\u2018&nbsp;\u201CSince I saw the blood of Naboth and the blood of
        his children yesterday,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201CI will requite it for
        you in this tract of land,\u201D declares Yahweh.\u2019 So then lift him
        out and throw him on the tract of land according to the word of Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "When Ahaziah king of Judah saw, he fled the way of Beth-Haggen. Jehu
        pursued after him and said, \u201CShoot him also, in the chariot.\u201D They
        shot him at the ascent of Gur which is in Ibleam, and he fled to Megiddo,
        but he died there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then his officers carried him to Jerusalem, and they buried him in
        his tomb with his ancestors in the city of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Jezebel Loses Her High Position'
      title: Jezebel Loses Her High Position
      number: 29
      content: 'In the eleventh year of Joram the son of Ahab, Ahaziah had become
        king over Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'When Jehu came to Jezreel, Jezebel heard of it, so she painted her
        eyes with black eye paint and adorned her head and looked through the window. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Now Jehu had come in the gate, so she said, \u201CIs it peace, O
        Zimri, murderer of his master?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "When he lifted up his face to the window, he asked, \u201CWho is
        with me?\u201D Two or three eunuchs looked down to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So he said, \u201CThrow her down.\u201D So they threw her down, and
        her blood spattered on the wall and on the horses, and they trampled her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then he came and ate and drank, and said, \u201CPlease take care
        of this cursed one and bury her, for she is the daughter of a king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'When they went to bury her, they could not find her, except the skull,
        the feet, and the palms of the hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "They returned and told him, and he said, \u201CThis is the word of
        Yahweh which he spoke by the hand of his servant Elijah the Tishbite, saying,
        \u2018On the plot of ground of Jezreel, the dogs shall eat the flesh of Jezebel.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So the dead body of Jezebel became dung on the surface spread on
        the field in the plot of ground of Jezreel, so one cannot say, \u201CThis
        is Jezebel.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehu Continues Purging the House of Ahab'
      title: Jehu Continues Purging the House of Ahab
      number: 1
      content: 'Ahab had seventy sons in Samaria, and Jehu wrote letters, and he
        sent them to Samaria to the officials of Jezreel, to the elders and to the
        guardians of Ahab, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CNow, when this letter comes to you and your master\u2019s sons
        are with you, the chariots are with you, the horses, a fortified city, and
        weapons, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "then you must select the best and the most suitable from the sons
        of your master, and you must place him on the throne of his father, and they
        must fight for the house of your masters.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But they were very afraid, and they said, \u201CLook, two kings could
        not stand before him; how can we stand?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So whoever was over the house, and whoever was over the city, and
        the elders and the guardians sent to Jehu, saying, \u201CWe are your servants;
        all that you say to us, we shall do. We shall not make anyone a king. Do
        what is good in your eyes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then he wrote to them a second letter, saying, \u201CIf you are for
        me, and you are listening to my voice, take the heads of the men of the sons
        of your master and come to me at this time tomorrow at Jezreel.\u201D Now
        the sons of the king, seventy men, were with the leaders of the city who
        were raising them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When the letter came to them, they took the sons of the king, and
        they killed seventy men. Then they put their heads in baskets and sent them
        to him at Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the messenger came and told him, saying, \u201CThey have brought
        the heads of the king\u2019s sons,\u201D and he said, \u201CPut them in two
        piles at the entrance of the gate until morning.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "It happened in the morning that he went out, stood, and said to all
        of the people, \u201CYou are righteous. Look, I conspired against my master
        and killed him. But who killed all of these? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Know then that the word of Yahweh will not fail which Yahweh spoke
        concerning the house of Ahab; Yahweh has done what he spoke by the hand of
        his servant Elijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Jehu killed all of the remainder of the house of Ahab in Jezreel,
        all of his leaders, his close friends, and his priests, until there was no
        survivor left for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then he arose and went and came to Samaria. On the way, he was at
        Beth-Eked of the shepherds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and Jehu met the brothers of Ahaziah king of Judah. He asked, \u201CWho
        are you?\u201D They said, \u201CWe are the brothers of Ahaziah; we came down
        for the peace of the king\u2019s children and the children of the queen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he said, \u201CSeize them alive!\u201D So they seized them alive
        but then slaughtered them at the cistern of Beth-Eked, forty-two men. He
        did not allow any of them to survive. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Next he went from there and found Jehonadab the son of Recab to meet
        him. He greeted him and asked him, \u201CIs your heart right with me as my
        heart is with you?\u201D Then Jehonadab said, \u201CYes, it is. Give your
        hand!\u201D And he gave his hand and took him up to him on the chariot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then he said, \u201CCome with me! Look at my zeal for Yahweh!\u201D
        So he let him ride in his chariot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Jehu Purges the Baal Worshipers'
      title: Jehu Purges the Baal Worshipers
      number: 17
      content: 'Then he came to Samaria and killed all who remained to Ahab in Samaria
        until he wiped them out according to the word of Yahweh which he had spoken
        to Elijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Jehu assembled all of the people and said to them, \u201CAhab
        served Baal a little, but Jehu will worship him greatly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So then, summon to me all of the prophets of Baal and all of his
        servants and his priests; no man should fail to come, for I have a great
        sacrifice for Baal. Anyone who fails to come shall not live!\u201D Now Jehu
        was acting with cunning in order to destroy the servants of Baal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Jehu said, \u201CSanctify a solemn assembly for Baal!\u201D
        So they proclaimed it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Jehu sent word through all of Israel, and all of the servants of
        Baal came; there did not remain a man who did not come. They came to the
        house of Baal so that the house of Baal was filled from wall to wall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He said to the one who was over the wardrobe, \u201CBring out clothing
        for all of the servants of Baal.\u201D So he brought the clothing out for
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Jehu and Jehonadab the son of Recab came to the temple of Baal,
        and he said to the servants of Baal, \u201CSearch and see that there is none
        of the servants of Yahweh here with you; only those who serve Baal.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "They came to offer sacrifices and burnt offerings. Now Jehu had stationed
        for himself eighty men outside, and he said, \u201CThe man who lets anyone
        escape from the men who I am entrusting to you, he will pay with his life!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "It happened that when he finished offering the burnt offering, Jehu
        said to the royal guard and to the officers, \u201CCome and kill them; let
        no man go free!\u201D So they put them to the sword, and the royal guard
        and the officers threw them out, then they went up to the citadel of the
        temple of Baal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'They brought out the stone pillars of the temple of Baal and burned
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So they broke down the stone pillars of Baal and destroyed the temple
        of Baal and made it into a latrine until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Jehu wiped out Baal from Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Only Jehu did not turn aside from the sins of Jeroboam the son of
        Nebat by which he caused Israel to sin; namely, the calf-shaped idols of
        gold which were in Bethel and Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Yahweh said to Jehu, \u201CBecause you have done well by doing right
        in my eyes and you have done to the house of Ahab according to all that was
        in my heart; therefore, sons of the fourth generation will sit for you on
        the throne of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'But Jehu was not careful to walk in the law of Yahweh God of Israel
        with all his heart; he did not turn from the sins of Jeroboam by which he
        caused Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'In those days, Yahweh began to reduce Israel, so Hazael defeated
        them in every territory of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'from the Jordan eastward: all of the land of Gilead, the Gadites,
        the Reubenites, and the Manassites, from Aroer which is on the Wadi Arnon
        and Gilead and Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Jehu and all that he did and all
        of his powerful deeds, are they not written in the scroll of the events of
        the days of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So Jehu slept with his ancestors, and they buried him in Samaria,
        and Jehoahaz his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Now the days which Jehu had reigned over Israel were twenty-eight
        years in Samaria. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Athaliah Usurps the Throne in Judah'
      title: Athaliah Usurps the Throne in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, so
        she prepared to destroy all of the offspring of the royal family. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But Jehosheba the daughter of King Joram and sister of Ahaziah took
        Jehoash the son of Ahaziah, and she stole him from among the sons of the
        king who were being put to death, putting him and his nurse in the inner
        bedroom. So they hid him from the presence of Athaliah, and he was not killed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He remained with her in the temple of Yahweh, hidden for six years
        while Athaliah was reigning over the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But in the seventh year Jehoiada sent and took the commanders of
        the hundreds of the Carites and the runners, and he brought them to himself
        to the temple of Yahweh. Then he made a covenant with them and made them
        swear in the house of Yahweh and showed them the son of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He commanded them, saying, \u201CThis is the thing which you must
        do: one third of you who go off duty on the Sabbath, the keepers of the guard
        in the house of the king, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and another third at the gate of Sur, and a third at the gate behind
        the runners, shall guard the post of the palace alternately. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Two of the units among you, all who go on duty on the Sabbath, guard
        the post of the temple of Yahweh for the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You must surround the king all about, each with his weapon in his
        hand; whoever comes to the ranks must be killed. Be with the king wherever
        he goes.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the commanders of hundreds did according to all that Jehoiada
        the priest commanded, and each took his men who went off duty on the Sabbath
        and those who came on duty on the Sabbath, and they came to Jehoiada the
        priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the priest gave to the commanders of the hundreds spears and
        small round shields which were King David\u2019s, which were in the temple
        of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So the royal runners stood, each with his weapons in his hand, from
        the side of the temple to the south up to the side of the temple on the north,
        around the altar and around the temple, about the king all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then he brought out the son of the king, put the crown on him with
        the testimony, and they made him king, anointed him, clapped their hands,
        and said, \u201CLong live the king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When Athaliah heard the sound of the runners of the people, she came
        to the people at the temple of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "She looked, and there was the king standing by the pillar according
        to the custom. The commanders and the trumpeters were by the king, and all
        of the people of the land were rejoicing and blowing on the trumpets. Athaliah
        tore her clothes and she called, \u201CTreason, treason!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Jehoiada the priest commanded the commanders of the hundreds,
        the appointed of the army, and he said to them, \u201CBring her out to the
        house of the ranks! The one coming after her should kill her with the sword,\u201D
        for the priest had said, \u201CLet her not be killed in the temple of Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So they grabbed her as she went by the entranceway of the horses
        to the palace of the king, and she was killed there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Jehoiada made a covenant between Yahweh and the king and the
        people, that the people should be as a people for Yahweh, and also a covenant
        between the king and the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then all the people of the land went to the temple of Baal and tore
        it down, and its altars and its images they broke completely into pieces.
        Mattan the priest of Baal they killed in front of the altars. Then the priest
        put guards over the house of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He took the commanders of the hundreds and the Carites and the runners
        and all the people of the land, and they brought the king down from the temple
        of Yahweh. And they marched by the way of the runner\u2019s gate to the palace
        of the king, and he sat on the throne of the kings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'All the people of the land rejoiced, and the city rested; for Athaliah
        had been killed with the sword in the palace of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: ' Jehoash was seven years old when he began to reign. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoash/Joash Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jehoash/Joash Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'In the seventh year of Jehu, Jehoash became king. He reigned in Jerusalem
        forty years, and the name of his mother was Zibiah from Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Jehoash did right in the eyes of Yahweh all of his days, because
        Jehoiada the priest instructed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Temple Repairs Planned'
      title: Temple Repairs Planned
      number: 3
      content: 'Only the high places were not removed; the people were still making
        sacrifices and offering incense on the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jehoash said to the priests, \u201CAll of the money for the sacred
        things that is brought to the temple of Yahweh, the money taxed at its proper
        value for each person and all of the money which comes upon the heart of
        a man to bring to the temple of Yahweh, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "let the priests take for themselves, each from his treasurers, and
        let them repair the breach of the temple for every place where damage is
        found.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'It happened in the twenty-third year of King Jehoash that the priests
        had not repaired the damage in the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So King Jehoash summoned Jehoiada the priest and the priests, and
        he said to them, \u201CWhy are you not repairing the damage in the temple?
        Now, you shall not take money from your treasurers for the damage in the
        temple. You must provide it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the priests agreed not to take money from the people and not to
        repair the damage to the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Jehoiada the priest took a certain chest and bored a hole in
        its lid, and he put it beside the altar to the right as a man enters into
        the temple of Yahweh; then the priests who were keepers of the threshold
        would put there all of the money brought into the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'It happened that when they saw a great deal of money in the chest,
        the secretary of the king and the high priest would come up, put the money
        in bags, then count the money found in the temple of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They placed the money, which was weighed out, into the hands of the
        workers who were appointed over the temple of Yahweh, and they paid it to
        the skilled craftsmen of wood and to the builders working on the temple of
        Yahweh '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and to the masons and the stonecutters, to buy timber and stones
        for hewing, in order to repair the damage of the temple of Yahweh, and for
        all who went to the temple to repair it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Only, for the temple of Yahweh, there were not any silver basins,
        snuffers, bowls for drinking wine, trumpets, or any vessel of gold or silver
        from the money being brought to the temple of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For they gave that to all the workers, and they repaired the temple
        of Yahweh with it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They did not have to settle accounts with the men into whose hands
        they placed the money to give to the workers, for they were dealing honestly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Hazael Threatens Judah'
      title: Hazael Threatens Judah
      number: 16
      content: 'The money of the guilt offering and the money of the sin offering
        was not brought into the temple of Yahweh, but were each for the priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'At that time, Hazael king of Aram went up and fought against Gath
        and captured it; then Hazael set his face to go up against Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Jehoash king of Judah took all of the holy objects that Jehoshaphat,
        Joram, and Ahaziah his ancestors, the kings of Judah, had devoted, and all
        his holy objects and all of the gold found in the treasuries of the temple
        of Yahweh, and in the palace of the king, and he sent them to Hazael king
        of Aram, so that he went up from Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Joash and all that he did, are they
        not written in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then his servants arose and conspired and killed Joash in the house
        of the Millo as he was going down toward Silla. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Jozabad the son of Shimeath and Jehozabad the son of Shomer, his
        servants, struck him and killed him, so they buried him with his ancestors
        in the city of David. Then Amaziah his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoahaz and Jehoash in Israel'
      title: Jehoahaz and Jehoash in Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'In the twenty-third year of Joash the son of Ahaziah, king of Judah,
        Jehoahaz the son of Jehu became king over Israel in Samaria, reigning seventeen
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But he did evil in the eyes of Yahweh, and he went after the sins
        of Jeroboam the son of Nebat with which he had caused Israel to sin, and
        he did not depart from it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So the anger of Yahweh was kindled against Israel, and he gave them
        into the hand of Hazael king of Aram and into the hand of Ben-Hadad the son
        of Hazael repeatedly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Jehoahaz entreated Yahweh, and Yahweh listened to him, for he
        saw the oppression of Israel, because the king of Aram oppressed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Yahweh gave Israel a savior, and they went out from under the hand
        of Aram. So the Israelites lived in their tents as formerly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Yet they did not depart from the sins of the house of Jeroboam which
        he caused Israel to sin, but walked in it; and also, the pole of the Asherah
        worship was still standing in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For there was no army left over for Jehoahaz except for fifty horsemen,
        ten chariots, and ten thousand infantry, for the king of Aram had destroyed
        them and made them as the dust at threshing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Jehoahaz and all that he did and
        his powerful deeds, are they not written in the scroll of the events of the
        days of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Jehoahaz slept with his ancestors and they buried him in Samaria,
        and Jehoash his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In the thirty-seventh year of Joash king of Judah, Jehoash the son
        of Jehoahaz became king over Israel in Samaria, reigning sixteen years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh; he did not depart from all of
        the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat which he caused Israel to sin, but
        walked in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Joash and all that he did, his powerful
        deeds, and how he fought with Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written
        in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Elisha Passes Away'
      title: Elisha Passes Away
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Joash slept with his ancestors, and Jeroboam sat on his throne.
        Joash was buried in Samaria with the kings of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Elisha became ill with the illness with which he would die, so Jehoash
        king of Israel went down to him and wept before him, and said, \u201CMy father,
        my father; the chariot of Israel and its horsemen!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Elisha said to him, \u201CTake a bow and arrows,\u201D so he took
        him a bow and arrows. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He said to the king of Israel, \u201CLay your hand on the bow,\u201D
        so he lay hold of it; then Elisha put his hand on the hands of the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he said, \u201COpen the window to the east,\u201D so he opened
        it. Elisha said, \u201CShoot,\u201D and he shot. Then he said, \u201CAn arrow
        of victory for Yahweh, and an arrow of victory against Aram; you shall fight
        the Arameans in Aphek until finishing them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then he said, \u201CTake the arrows,\u201D so he took them. He said
        to the king of Israel, \u201CStrike the ground,\u201D so he struck three
        times and stopped. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Yet the man of God became angry against him and said, \u201CFor striking
        five or six times, then you would have defeated Aram until finishing them,
        but now you will defeat Aram only three times.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Elisha died and they buried him. Now the raiding parties of Moab
        came in the spring.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And it happened that they were burying a man; suddenly they saw the
        marauding band, so they threw the man in the grave of Elisha. As he went
        in, the man touched the bones of Elisha, and became alive and got up on his
        feet! '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Hazael king of Aram oppressed Israel all the days of Jehoahaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But Yahweh had mercy on them and showed compassion to them and turned
        to them because of his covenant with Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. He was not
        willing to destroy them nor cast them from his presence up to now. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Hazael king of Aram died, his son Ben-Hadad became king in his
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz returned and took the cities from the
        hand of Ben-Hadad the son of Hazael which he had taken from the hand of Jehoahaz
        his father in the war. Three times Jehoash defeated him and recovered the
        towns of Israel. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Amaziah Reigns in Judah; Jeroboam II in Israel'
      title: Amaziah Reigns in Judah; Jeroboam II in Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'In the second year of Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz king of Israel,
        Amaziah the son of Jehoash king of Judah began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He was twenty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        twenty-nine years in Jerusalem; and the name of his mother was Jehoaddin
        from Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He did right in the eyes of Yahweh, only not as David his ancestor;
        as all which Jehoash his father had done, he did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Only the high places were not removed; the people were still sacrificing
        and offering incense on the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'It happened that when the kingdom was firmly in his hand, he killed
        his servants who had killed his father the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But the sons of the killers he did not kill, as it is written in
        the scroll of the law of Moses which Yahweh had commanded, saying, \u201CFathers
        should not be killed because of children, and children should not be killed
        because of fathers; but a man should die because of his own sin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He also killed ten thousand Edomites in the Valley of Salt, and he
        seized Sela in the battle, and he called its name Jokteel, until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Amaziah sent messengers to Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz the son
        of Jehu king of Israel, saying, \u201CCome let us meet face-to-face.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Jehoash the king of Israel sent to Amaziah, saying, \u201CThe
        thornbush which is in Lebanon sent to the cedar which is in Lebanon, saying,
        \u2018Give your daughter to my son as wife,\u2019 but an animal of the field
        which is in Lebanon passed by and trampled the thornbush. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You have indeed defeated Edom and your heart is lifted up; enjoy
        the honor and stay home. Why should you provoke trouble so that you fall
        and Judah with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But Amaziah would not listen, so Jehoash king of Israel went up and
        they met face-to-face, he and Amaziah king of Judah, at Beth-Shemesh which
        belongs to Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Judah was defeated before Israel and they fled, each to this tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Jehoash king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the son of
        Jehoash, the son of Ahaziah, at Beth-Shemesh. Then they came to Jerusalem,
        and he broke down the wall of Jerusalem from the Gate of Ephraim up to the
        Corner Gate, four hundred cubits! '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He also took all of the gold and silver and all the vessels found
        in the temple of Yahweh and in the treasury rooms of the palace of the king,
        as well as the hostages; then he returned to Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Jehoash which he did, and his powerful
        deeds, and how he fought with Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written
        on the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Azariah Succeeds Amaziah in Jerusalem; Zechariah Succeeds Jeroboam
        II in Samaria'
      title: Azariah Succeeds Amaziah in Jerusalem; Zechariah Succeeds Jeroboam II
        in Samaria
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Jehoash slept with his ancestors and was buried in Samaria with
        the kings of Israel, and Jeroboam his son reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Amaziah the son of Jehoash king of Judah lived fifteen years after
        the death of Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Amaziah, are they not written on the
        scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They conspired against him in Jerusalem, so he fled to Lachish. But
        they sent men after him to Lachish, and they killed him there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then they carried him on the horses, and he was buried with his ancestors
        in the city of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'All of the people of Judah took sixteen-year-old Azariah and made
        him king in place of this father Amaziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He rebuilt Elath and restored it to Judah after the king slept with
        his ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In the fifteenth year of Amaziah the son of Jehoash king of Judah,
        Jeroboam the son of Jehoash king of Israel began to reign in Samaria, reigning
        forty-one years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But he did evil in the eyes of Yahweh; he did not depart from all
        the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat which he caused Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He restored the boundary of Israel from Lebo-Hamath up to the sea
        of the Arabah, according to the word of Yahweh which he spoke by the hand
        of his servant Jonah the son of Amittai the prophet, who was from Gath-Hepher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For Yahweh saw that the misery of Israel was very bitter, whether
        bond or free, but there was no helper for Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Yahweh did not decree to blot out the name of Israel from under the
        heavens, so he saved them by the hand of Jeroboam the son of Jehoash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Jeroboam, all that he did, his powerful
        deeds, how he fought, and how he restored Damascus and Hamath of Judah to
        Israel, are they not written on the scroll of the events of the days of the
        kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So Jeroboam slept with his ancestors the kings of Israel, and his
        son Zechariah became king in his place. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Acts of Azariah (Uzziah) in Judah'
      title: The Acts of Azariah (Uzziah) in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'In the twenty-seventh year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Azariah the
        son of Amaziah king of Judah began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He was sixteen years old when he became king, and he reigned fifty-two
        years in Jerusalem. The name of his mother was Jecoliah of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He did right in the eyes of Yahweh, according to all that Amaziah
        his father had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Only he did not remove the high places; the people were still sacrificing
        and burning incense on the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Yahweh struck the king, and he was infected with a skin disease until
        the day of his death. He lived in a separate house, while Jotham the son
        of the king was over the house, governing the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Azariah, and all that he did, are they
        not written on the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Zechariah in Israel'
      title: Zechariah in Israel
      number: 7
      content: 'So Azariah slept with his ancestors, and they buried him with his
        ancestors in the city of David, and Jotham his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the thirty-eighth year of Azariah king of Judah, Zechariah the
        son of Jeroboam reigned over Israel in Samaria for six months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh as his ancestors had done. He did
        not depart from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat which he caused Israel
        to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Shallum the son of Jabesh conspired against him, struck him in front
        of the people, killed him, and reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Zechariah, look, they are written
        on the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Shallum Reigns only a Month in Israel'
      title: Shallum Reigns only a Month in Israel
      number: 12
      content: "This is the word of Yahweh which he spoke to Jehu, saying, \u201CSons
        of a fourth generation shall sit for you on the throne of Israel,\u201D and
        it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Shallum the son of Jabesh began to reign in the thirty-ninth year
        of Uzziah king of Judah, and he reigned a full month in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Menahem the son of Gadi came up from Tirzah, and he came to
        Samaria and struck down Shallum the son of Jabesh in Samaria and killed him.
        Then he became king in place of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Shallum, and his conspiracy which
        he conspired; look, they are written on the scroll of the events of the days
        of the kings of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Menahem Reigns in Israel'
      title: Menahem Reigns in Israel
      number: 16
      content: 'At that time Menahem destroyed Tiphsah, all who were in it, and all
        its territory from Tirzah, because it had not opened to him, so he destroyed
        it and ripped open all of its pregnant women. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'In the thirty-ninth year of Azariah king of Judah, Menahem the son
        of Gadi began to reign over Israel for ten years in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But he did evil in the eyes of Yahweh. He did not depart all of his
        days from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat which he caused Israel to
        sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Pul the king of Assyria came against the land, so Menahem gave a
        thousand talents of silver to Pul so that his hand would be with him to strengthen
        his hold on the kingdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Menahem exacted the money from Israel, from all the very rich, to
        give to the king of Assyria fifty shekels of silver for each one. Then the
        king of Assyria returned and did not stay there in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Menahem, and all that he did, are they
        not written in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Pekahiah Reigns in Israel'
      title: Pekahiah Reigns in Israel
      number: 22
      content: 'So Menahem slept with his ancestors, and Pekahiah his son became
        king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In the fiftieth year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekahiah the son of
        Menahem began to reign over Israel in Samaria for two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But he did evil in the eyes of Yahweh. He did not depart from the
        sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat which he caused Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Pekah the son of Remaliah, his captain, conspired against him, so
        he attacked him in Samaria in the citadel fortress of the palace of the king,
        with Argob and Arieh. With him also were fifty men from the children of the
        Gileadites, and he killed him and became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Pekah Reigns in Israel'
      title: Pekah Reigns in Israel
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Pekahiah and all that he did, look,
        they are written in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'In the fifty-second year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekah the son
        of Remaliah began to reign over Israel in Samaria for twenty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh. He did not depart from the sins
        of Jeroboam the son of Nebat which he caused Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'In the days of Pekah king of Israel, Tiglath-Pileser the king of
        Assyria came and took Ijon, Abel-Beth-Maacah, Janoah, Kedesh, Hazor, the
        Gilead, the Galilee, and all the land of Naphtali; then he deported them
        to Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Hoshea the son of Elah conspired against Pekah the son of Remaliah,
        and he attacked and killed him. He reigned in place of him in the twentieth
        year of Jotham the son of Uzziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Jotham Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jotham Reigns in Judah
      number: 31
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Pekah and all that he did, look,
        they are written in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'In the second year of Pekah the son of Remaliah, king of Israel,
        Jotham the son of Uzziah king of Judah began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        sixteen years in Jerusalem, and the name of his mother was Jerusha the daughter
        of Zadok. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'He did what was right in the eyes of Yahweh, according to all that
        Uzziah his father had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Only the high places were not removed; the people still were sacrificing
        and offering incense on the high places. He built the upper gate of the temple
        of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Jotham which he did, are they not
        written on the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '(Now, in those days, Yahweh began to send Rezin the king of Aram
        and Pekah the son of Remaliah against Judah.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So Jotham slept with his ancestors and was buried with his ancestors
        in the city of David his ancestor, and his son Ahaz became king in his place. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ahaz Reigns in Judah and Seeks Help against the Assyrians'
      title: Ahaz Reigns in Judah and Seeks Help against the Assyrians
      number: 1
      content: 'In the seventeenth year of Pekah the son of Remaliah, Ahaz the son
        of Jotham king of Judah began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Ahaz was twenty years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        sixteen years in Jerusalem. He did not do right in the eyes of Yahweh his
        God as David his ancestor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He walked in the way of the kings of Israel; he even let his son
        pass through the fire according to the detestable things of the nations which
        Yahweh drove out from before the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He sacrificed and offered incense on the high places, on the hills,
        and under every green tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Rezin the king of Aram went up with Pekah the son of Remaliah
        king of Israel against Jerusalem for battle, and they besieged Ahaz but were
        not able to defeat him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'At that time, Rezin king of Aram recovered Elath for Aram and drove
        out the Judeans from Elath. The Arameans came to Elath and have lived there
        until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Ahaz sent messengers to Tiglath-Pileser king of Assyria, saying,
        \u201CI am your servant and your son. Come up and rescue me from the hand
        of the king of Aram and from the hand of the king of Israel who are rising
        up against me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ahaz took the silver and gold found in the house of Yahweh and in
        the treasury rooms of the palace of the king, and he sent a gift to the king
        of Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Damascus Falls to the Assyrians'
      title: Damascus Falls to the Assyrians
      number: 9
      content: 'So the king of Assyria listened to him and he went up to Damascus
        and captured it and deported them to Kir. He also killed Rezin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So King Ahaz went to meet Tiglath-Pileser the king of Assyria in
        Damascus, and he saw the altar which was in Damascus, so King Ahaz sent to
        Uriah the priest the builder\u2019s plan of the altar and the exact model
        of how it had been made.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Uriah the priest built the altar according to all that King Ahaz
        had sent from Damascus; thus Uriah the priest did before King Ahaz came from
        Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When the king came from Damascus, the king saw the altar, so he went
        near to the altar and went up on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then he offered his burnt offerings and his grain offerings, he poured
        his libations and dashed the blood of his fellowship offerings against the
        altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now the bronze altar which was before Yahweh, he brought over from
        the front of the temple, from between his altar and the temple of Yahweh,
        and he placed it at the side of his altar to the north. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then King Ahaz commanded Uriah the priest, saying, \u201COn the great
        altar burn the morning burnt offering and the grain offering of the evening,
        the burnt offering of the king and his grain offering, the burnt offering
        of all of the people of the land, their offerings, their libations, and all
        of the blood of the burnt offerings, the blood of the sacrifices you must
        dash on it. But the bronze altar shall be for me to inquire by.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Uriah the priest did according to all that King Ahaz commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then King Ahaz cut off the side panels of the water carts and removed
        from upon them the basin, and the sea he took down from the bronze oxen that
        were under it and put it on a stone base. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The covering for the Sabbath which they had built in the palace and
        in the entrance of the king to the outside, he removed from the temple of
        Yahweh because of the presence of the king of Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Ahaz which he did, are they not
        written in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Ahaz slept with his ancestors and was buried with his ancestors
        in the city of David, and Hezekiah his son reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hoshea Reigns in Israel'
      title: Hoshea Reigns in Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'In the twelfth year of Ahaz the king of Judah, Hoshea the son of
        Elah began to reign over Israel in Samaria, reigning nine years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh, only not as the kings of Israel
        who were before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Shalmaneser the king of Assyria came up against him, and Hoshea became
        his vassal and paid tribute to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the king of Assyria found treachery in Hoshea, for he had sent
        messengers to So king of Egypt, and he did not offer tribute to the king
        of Assyria as he had year after year; so the king of Assyria arrested him,
        and confined him in a house of imprisonment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Israel Deported to Assyria and the Reasons It Fell'
      title: Israel Deported to Assyria and the Reasons It Fell
      number: 5
      content: 'So the king of Assyria went up in all the land, then he went up to
        Samaria and besieged it for three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In the ninth year of Hoshea, the king of Assyria captured Samaria
        and deported Israel to Assyria. He placed them in Halah, in Habor, in the
        river regions of Gozan, and in the cities of the Medes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now this happened because the Israelites had sinned against Yahweh
        their God when he brought them up from the land of Egypt from under the hand
        of Pharaoh the king of Egypt and they feared other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They walked in the statutes of the nations whom Yahweh had driven
        out from before the Israelites, which the kings of Israel had introduced. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Israelites secretly did things which were not right, against
        Yahweh their God; they built high places for themselves in all their towns,
        from the watchtower up to the fortified city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They set up for themselves stone pillars and poles of Asherah worship
        on every high hill and under every green tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They burned incense there on all the high places, like the nations
        which Yahweh deported before them, and they did evil things to provoke Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They served idols which Yahweh had said to them, \u201CYou shall
        not do this thing!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yahweh warned Israel and Judah by the hand of his every prophet,
        with every seer saying, \u201CTurn from all of your evil ways, and keep my
        commandments and my ordinances, according to all the law which I commanded
        your ancestors, which I sent to you by the hand of my servants the prophets.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But they did not listen and they stiffened their necks, like the
        necks of their ancestors who did not believe in Yahweh their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They rejected his statutes, his covenant which he made with their
        ancestors, and his warnings which he gave to them; and they went after the
        idols, became vain, and went after all the nations which were all around
        them, which Yahweh had commanded them not to do as they did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They abandoned all the commands of Yahweh their God and made for
        themselves two molten calf-shaped idols; they made a pole of Asherah worship
        and bowed down to the army of the heavens and served Baal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They made their sons and their daughters pass through the fire, they
        practiced divination and read omens, and they sold themselves to do evil
        in the eyes of Yahweh to provoke him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So Yahweh was very angry with Israel and he removed them from his
        presence; none remained except the tribe of Judah alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Even Judah did not keep the commands of Yahweh their God, and they
        walked in the customs of Israel which they introduced, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'so Yahweh rejected all the offspring of Israel and punished them,
        and he gave them into the hand of the plunderers until he banished them from
        his presence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For he had torn Israel from the house of David, and they made Jeroboam
        the son of Nebat king, but Jeroboam detached Israel from following Yahweh,
        and he made them sin a great sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The Israelites walked in all the sins of Jeroboam which he committed,
        and they did not depart from it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Israel Repopulated with Foreign Captives'
      title: Israel Repopulated with Foreign Captives
      number: 23
      content: 'until Yahweh removed Israel from his presence as he had foretold
        by the hand of all his servants, the prophets. And so he deported Israel
        from upon his land to Assyria until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The king of Assyria brought from Babylonia, from Cush, from Arva,
        from Hamath, and Sepharvaim, and he settled them in the cities of Samaria
        in place of the Israelites, so they took possession of Samaria and lived
        in her cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'It happened that when they began living there, they did not fear
        Yahweh, so Yahweh sent lions among them, and they were killing them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So they said to the king of Assyria, \u201CThe nations whom you deported
        and settled in the cities of Samaria do not know the customs of the God of
        the land, so he sent lions among them, and now they are killing them because
        they do not know the customs of the God of the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the king of Assyria commanded, saying, \u201CRelease one of
        the priests whom you deported from there, and let him go and settle there.
        Let him teach them the customs of the God of the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So one of the priests went, whom they had deported from Samaria,
        and he settled in Bethel and was teaching them how they should fear Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Yet every nation was making their gods, and they put them in the
        shrine of the high places that the Samaritans had made, every nation in their
        cities in which they were living. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The men of Babylonia made Succoth Benoth; the men of Cush made Nergal;
        the men of Hamath made Ashima. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The Arvites made Nibhaz and Tartak; the Sepharvites were burning
        their children in the fire to Adrammelech and Anammelech the gods of Sepharvaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Those who were fearing Yahweh made priests of the high places from
        among themselves, and they were sacrificing for them in the shrines of the
        high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Yahweh they were fearing, but their gods they were serving, according
        to the customs of the nations from which they were deported. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Until this day they are doing according to their former customs;
        none of them are fearing Yahweh, and none of them are doing according to
        their statutes, to their decisions, to the law, or to the commands that Yahweh
        commanded the descendants of Jacob to which he had given the name Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Yahweh had made a covenant with them and commanded them, \u201CYou
        shall not fear other gods, nor shall you bow down to them, nor shall you
        serve them, nor shall you sacrifice to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Rather, Yahweh, who brought you out from the land of Egypt with great
        strength and with an outstretched arm\u2014him you shall fear, and to him
        you shall bow down, and to him you shall sacrifice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The statutes, the decisions, the law, and the commands that he wrote
        to you, you shall observe to do always, and you shall not fear other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The covenant that I have made with you, you shall not forget, and
        you shall not fear other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But Yahweh your God you shall fear, and he will deliver you from
        the hand of all of your enemies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'They did not listen but kept on doing according to their former customs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "So these nations were fearing Yahweh, but they were serving their
        idols, as were their children and their children\u2019s children; as their
        ancestors did, they are doing until this day. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hezekiah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Hezekiah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'It happened in the third year of Hoshea the son of Elah king of Israel,
        that Hezekiah the son of Ahaz king of Judah became king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. The name of his mother was Abi, the daughter
        of Zechariah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He did right in the eyes of Yahweh according to all that David his
        ancestor had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He removed the high places, and he smashed the stone pillars; he
        cut down the poles of Asherah worship and demolished the bronze serpent which
        Moses had made, for up to those days the Israelites were offering incense
        to it and called it Nehushtan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He trusted in Yahweh the God of Israel; there was no one like him,
        before or after, among all the kings of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He held on to Yahweh; he did not depart from following him, and he
        kept his commands that Yahweh had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Yahweh was with him; everywhere he went, he succeeded. He rebelled
        against the king of Assyria and did not serve him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He attacked the Philistines up to Gaza and its territory from the
        watchtower up to the fortified city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'It happened in the fourth year of King Hezekiah, that is, the seventh
        year of Hoshea the son of Elah king of Israel, Shalmaneser king of Assyria
        came against Samaria and laid siege against her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'At the end of three years, he captured it in the sixth year of Hezekiah,
        that is, the ninth year of Hoshea king of Israel; Samaria was captured. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the king of Assyria deported Israel to Assyria and settled them
        in Halah, in Habor, in the river regions of Gozan, and in the cities of the
        Medes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Sennacherib of Assyria Invades Judah'
      title: Sennacherib of Assyria Invades Judah
      number: 12
      content: 'because they did not listen to the voice of Yahweh their God, and
        they transgressed his covenant; all that he had commanded Moses, the servant
        of Yahweh, they did not listen to nor did they obey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'In the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah, Sennacherib king of Assyria
        came up against all of the fortified cities of Judah and captured them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Hezekiah king of Judah sent word to the king of Assyria at Lachish,
        saying, \u201CI have done wrong. Withdraw from me. What you impose on me
        I will bear.\u201D So the king of Assyria imposed on Hezekiah king of Judah
        three hundred talents of silver and thirty talents of gold. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Hezekiah gave all of the silver found in the temple of Yahweh
        and in the storerooms of the house of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'At that time, Hezekiah cut off the doors of the temple of Yahweh
        and the doorposts which Hezekiah king of Judah had overlaid, and he gave
        them to the king of Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So the king of Assyria sent the commander in chief, the chief eunuch,
        and the chief advisor from Lachish to King Hezekiah at Jerusalem with a heavy
        army. They went up and came to Jerusalem, then they went up and came and
        stood at the aqueduct of the upper pool which is on the main road of the
        washer\u2019s field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Assyrians Advise against Trust in Yahweh'
      title: Assyrians Advise against Trust in Yahweh
      number: 18
      content: 'Then they called to the king, so Eliakim the son of Hilkiah who was
        over the palace, Shebna the secretary, and Joah the son of Asaph the recorder,
        came out to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the chief advisor said to them, \u201CPlease say to Hezekiah:
        \u2018Thus says the great king, the king of Assyria: \u201CWhat is this confidence
        that you trust? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "You think only a word of lips, \u2018I have advice and power for
        the war.\u2019 Now, on whom do you trust that you have rebelled against me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now, look! You rely on the staff of this broken reed, on Egypt, which
        when a man leans on it, it goes into his hand and pierces it! So is Pharaoh
        the king of Egypt for all who are trusting on him! '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But if you say to me, \u2018On Yahweh our God we trust,\u2019 is
        it not he whose high places and altars Hezekiah removed, and he had said
        to Judah and to Jerusalem, \u2018In the presence of this altar you shall
        bow down only in Jerusalem?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So then, please make a wager with my lord, with the king of Assyria,
        and I will give to you a thousand horses if you are able on your part to
        put riders on them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'How can you repulse a single captain among the least of the servants
        of my master? Yet you rely for yourself on Egypt for chariots and horsemen! '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Have I now come up against this place without Yahweh to destroy it?
        Yahweh has said to me, \u2018Go up against this land and destroy it!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah and Shebna and Joah said to the chief
        commander, \u201CPlease speak to your servants in Aramaic, for we are understanding,
        but you must not speak Judean with us in the ears of the people who are on
        the wall.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The chief commander said to them, \u201CIs it solely to your master
        and to you my master has sent me to speak these words? Is it not for the
        men who sit on the wall to eat their feces and to drink their urine with
        you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then the chief commander stood and called with a great voice in Judean,
        and he spoke and said, \u201CHear the word of the king, the great king of
        Assyria! "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Thus says the king, \u2018Do not let Hezekiah deceive you, for he
        will not be able to rescue you from my hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Do not let Hezekiah make you trust in Yahweh, saying, \u201CCertainly
        Yahweh will rescue us, and this city shall not be given into the hand of
        the king of Assyria!\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Do not listen to Hezekiah; for thus says the king of Assyria, \u2018Make
        with me a treaty of peace and come out to me that each may eat from his vine
        and each from his fig tree, and each may drink water from his cistern! "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Until I come and take you to a land like your land, a land of grain
        and new wine, a land of bread and vineyards, a land of olive trees, olive
        oil, and honey, that you may live and not die! You must not listen to Hezekiah,
        for he has misled you by saying, \u201CYahweh will deliver us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Did the gods of each of the nations ever rescue the land from the
        hand of the king of Assyria? '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Where are the gods of Hamath and Arpad? Where are the gods of Sepharvaim,
        Hena, and Ivvah? For did they rescue Samaria from my hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Who among all of the gods of the countries have rescued their countries
        from my hand that Yahweh should rescue Jerusalem from my hand?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "The people were silent, and they did not answer him a word, for the
        command of that king was saying, \u201CYou shall not answer him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Eliakim the son of Hilkiah who was over the palace, and Shebna the
        secretary, and Joah the son of Asaph the recorder came to Hezekiah with torn
        clothes, and they told him the words of the chief commander. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaiah Sends Encouragement to Hezekiah'
      title: Isaiah Sends Encouragement to Hezekiah
      number: 1
      content: 'It happened that when King Hezekiah heard, he tore his clothes and
        covered himself with sackcloth and went to the temple of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He sent Eliakim who was over the palace, Shebna the secretary, the
        elders, and the priests, all clothed in sackcloth, to Isaiah the prophet
        the son of Amoz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They said to him, \u201CThus says Hezekiah, \u2018A day of distress,
        rebuke, and disgrace is this day, for the children are about to be born,
        but there is no strength to bear them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Perhaps Yahweh your God will hear all of the words of the chief commander
        whom his master the king of Assyria has sent to insult the living God, and
        he will rebuke the words which Yahweh your God has heard. Therefore lift
        up a prayer for the remainder who are left.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the servants of King Hezekiah came to Isaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and Isaiah said to them, \u201CThus you must say to your master,
        \u2018Thus says Yahweh, \u201CYou must not be afraid because the face of
        the words which you have heard, with which the servants of the king of Assyria
        have reviled me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Assyrians Defy God'
      title: The Assyrians Defy God
      number: 7
      content: "Look, I am putting in him a spirit. He will hear a rumor and return
        to his land. Then I will cause him to fall by the sword in his land.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When the chief commander returned, he found the king of Assyria fighting
        against Libnah, for he had heard that he had departed from Lachish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He heard about Tirhakah, the king of Cush, saying, \u201CLook, he
        has set out to fight with you,\u201D so he again sent messengers to Hezekiah,
        saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThus you shall say to Hezekiah the king of Judah, \u2018Let
        not your God whom you are trusting deceive you, by his saying, \u201CJerusalem
        shall not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Look, you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all the
        lands, by utterly destroying them, and shall you be delivered? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Did the gods of the nations that my predecessors destroyed deliver
        them? Not Gozan, Haran, Rezeph, nor the children of Eden who were in Tel
        Assar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Hezekiah Prays to Yahweh'
      title: Hezekiah Prays to Yahweh
      number: 13
      content: "Where are the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, the king of the
        city of Sepharvaim, Hena, and Ivvah?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Hezekiah took the letters from the hand of the messengers and read
        them. Then he went up to the temple of Yahweh, and Hezekiah spread them out
        before the presence of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Hezekiah prayed before the face of Yahweh and said, \u201CO
        Yahweh, God of Israel who lives above the cherubim. You are God, you alone,
        of all the kingdoms of the world; you have made the heavens and the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Incline your ears and hear; open, O Yahweh, your eyes and see and
        hear the words of Sennacherib which he has sent to insult the living God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Truly, O Yahweh, the kings of Assyria have utterly destroyed the
        nations and their land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He has hurled their gods in the fire because they are not gods, but
        the work of the hands of a human made of wood and stone, so they destroyed
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Isaiah Brings a Prophetic Response'
      title: Isaiah Brings a Prophetic Response
      number: 19
      content: "So then, O Yahweh our God, rescue us, please, from his hand, that
        all of the kingdoms of the earth may know that you, O Yahweh, you alone are
        God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Isaiah the son of Amoz sent to Hezekiah, saying, \u201CThus
        says Yahweh the God of Israel, \u2018What you have prayed to me about Sennacherib
        king of Assyria I have heard. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'This is the word that Yahweh has spoken concerning him: She despises
        you, she scorns you, the virgin daughter of Zion. Behind you the daughter
        of Jerusalem shakes her head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Whom have you mocked and reviled? And against whom have you have
        raised your voice and have haughtily lifted your eyes? Against the Holy One
        of Israel! '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "By the hand of your messengers you have mocked the Lord, and you
        have said, \u2018With my many chariots I have gone up to the height of the
        mountains. To the remote areas of Lebanon, I have felled the tallest of its
        cedars, the choicest of its cypresses. I have entered the place of overnight
        lodging. Even to the edge of forest of its fertile land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I dug wells and I drank foreign water, and I dried up with the sole
        of my steps all the canals of Egypt.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Have you not heard? From long ago I have determined it, from the
        days of old I have planned it, and now I am bringing it to pass. It shall
        be turned into a pile of rocks; fortified cities are ruined. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Their inhabitants, short of hand, shall be dismayed; and they shall
        be ashamed. They have become green plants of the open field, and tender grass,
        green grass of the roof and blight before the standing grain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Your sitting, your going out, and your coming in I know, and your
        raging against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Because you are raging against me, and your arrogance has come up
        in my ears, I will put my nose ring in your nose and my bridle in your mouth.
        And I will turn you back on the way that you have come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201C&nbsp;\u2018This will be the sign for you: Eat the volunteer
        plants for the year, and in the second year, the volunteer plants that spring
        up from that. But in the third year, sow and reap, plant vineyards and eat
        their fruit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The remainder of the house of Judah which survives will again take
        root below and bear fruit above. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For from Jerusalem a remnant shall go out and survivors from Mount
        Zion; the zeal of Yahweh will do this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201C&nbsp;\u2018Therefore thus says Yahweh to the king of Assyria,
        \u201CHe shall not come to this city, nor shall he shoot an arrow there,
        nor shall he bring a small shield near her, nor shall he cast a siege ramp
        against her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "By the way that he came to her he shall return; but to this city,
        he shall not come,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: An Angel Neutralizes the Assyrian Army'
      title: An Angel Neutralizes the Assyrian Army
      number: 34
      content: "And I will defend this city to save her for my sake and for the sake
        of David my servant.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'It happened in that night that an angel of Yahweh went out, and he
        struck down one hundred and eighty-five thousand in the camp of Assyria.
        When they got up early in the morning, look! All of them were dead corpses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then Sennacherib king of Assyria set out and went and returned and
        lived in Nineveh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'It happened that he was worshiping in the temple of Nisroch his god,
        and Adrammelech and Sharezer struck him with the sword. Then they escaped
        into the land of Ararat, and Esarhaddon his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hezekiah Loses Health and Regains It through Prayer'
      title: Hezekiah Loses Health and Regains It through Prayer
      number: 1
      content: "In those days Hezekiah became deathly ill, and Isaiah the son of
        Amoz the prophet came to him and said to him, \u201CThus says Yahweh, \u2018Command
        your house, for you are about to die; you will not recover.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then he turned his face to the wall and prayed to Yahweh, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CO Yahweh, please remember how I went about before you in faithfulness
        and with a whole heart, and remember the good that I have done in your eyes.\u201D
        Then Hezekiah wept bitterly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Isaiah had not gone out from the middle of the city when the word
        of Yahweh came to him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CReturn; you must say to Hezekiah, the leader of my people,
        \u2018Thus says Yahweh the God of David your ancestor, \u201CI have heard
        your prayer and I have seen your tears. Look, I am about to heal you. On
        the third day you shall go up to the temple of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I will add to your days fifteen years, and from the hand of the king
        of Assyria I will deliver you and this city. I will defend this city for
        my sake and for the sake of David my servant.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Isaiah said, \u201CBring a lump of figs,\u201D so they took
        and put it on the skin sores, and he lived. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201CWhat is the sign that Yahweh will
        heal me that I shall go up on the third day to the temple of Yahweh?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Isaiah said, \u201CThis is the sign for you from Yahweh that Yahweh
        will do the thing that he has promised: Shall the shadow advance ten steps
        or shall it return ten steps?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Hezekiah answered, \u201CIt is easy for the shadow to lengthen ten
        steps. No, but let the shadow return backwards ten steps.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Hezekiah Reveals Too Much to a Babylonian Envoy'
      title: Hezekiah Reveals Too Much to a Babylonian Envoy
      number: 11
      content: 'Isaiah the prophet called to Yahweh, and he brought back the shadow
        on the steps where it had gone down on the steps of Ahaz, backwards ten steps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'At that time, Berodak-Baladan the son of Baladan king of Babylon
        sent letters and a gift to Hezekiah, for he had heard that Hezekiah had been
        ill. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hezekiah heard about them and showed them all of the house of his
        treasure, both the silver and the gold, the spices, the good olive oil, the
        room of his weapons, and all that could be found in his treasuries. There
        was nothing that he did not show them in his palace and in all of his kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Isaiah the prophet came to King Hezekiah and said to him, \u201CWhat
        did these men say, and from where have they come to you?\u201D Hezekiah said,
        \u201CFrom a far land; they have come from Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then he asked, \u201CWhat did they see in your palace?\u201D And
        Hezekiah said, \u201CAll that is in my palace they have seen; there is nothing
        that I did not show them in my treasuries.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201CHear the word of Yahweh! "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Look, days are coming when all that is in your palace will
        be carried off; even all that your ancestors have stored up until this day,
        to Babylon; nothing shall be left,\u2019 says Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018Your sons who went out from you, whom you brought forth, will
        be taken, and they shall be eunuchs in the temple of the king of Babylon.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201CThe word of Yahweh which you
        have spoken is good,\u201D and he thought, \u201CIs it not that peace and
        security shall be in my days?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now the remainder of the acts of Hezekiah, all of his powerful deeds,
        and how he made the pool and the conduit and brought the water into the city,
        are they not written in the scroll of the events of the days of the kings
        of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Hezekiah slept with his ancestors, and Manasseh his son became
        king in his place. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Evil Manasseh Reigns after Godly Hezekiah'
      title: Evil Manasseh Reigns after Godly Hezekiah
      number: 1
      content: 'Manasseh was twelve years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        fifty-five years in Jerusalem. The name of his mother was Hephzibah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh, according to the detestable things
        of the nations that Yahweh had driven out from the presence of the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He returned and rebuilt the high places which Hezekiah his father
        had destroyed. He erected altars for Baal and made a pole of Asherah worship
        just as Ahab king of Israel had made, and he bowed down to all of the host
        of heaven and served them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He built altars in the temple of Yahweh about which Yahweh had said,
        \u201CI will put my name in Jerusalem.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He built an altar to all of the host of heaven in the two courtyards
        of the temple of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He made his son pass through the fire, practiced soothsaying and
        divination, and dealt with mediums and spiritists. He increased the doing
        of evil in the eyes of Yahweh to provoke him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He put the image of the Asherah that he had made in the temple which
        Yahweh had said to David and to Solomon his son, \u201CIn this temple and
        in Jerusalem which I have chosen from all of the tribes of Israel, I will
        put my name forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I will not again make the feet of Israel wander from the land which
        I have given to their ancestors, if they only observe to do according to
        all that I have commanded them, as far as the law that Moses my servant commanded
        them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Yahweh Sends a Rebuke to Manasseh'
      title: Yahweh Sends a Rebuke to Manasseh
      number: 9
      content: 'But Manasseh did not listen and tempted them to do evil more than
        the nations that Yahweh destroyed before the presence of the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Yahweh spoke by the hand of his servants the prophets, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBecause Manasseh the king of Judah committed these detestable
        things and did evil more than the Amorites did who were before him and caused
        even Judah to sin with his idols, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "therefore, thus says Yahweh the God of Israel, \u2018Look, I am bringing
        disaster upon Jerusalem and Judah about which the two ears of all who hear
        it will tingle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will stretch out over Jerusalem the measuring line of Samaria and
        the plumb line of the house of Ahab, and I will wipe Jerusalem as one wipes
        the dish; he wipes it and turns it on its face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will give up the remainder of my inheritance, and I will give them
        into the hand of their enemies. They shall become as prey and as spoil for
        all their enemies, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "because they have done evil in my eyes and were provoking me from
        the day that their ancestors came out from Egypt up to this day.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Moreover, Manasseh shed very much innocent blood until he filled
        Jerusalem from one end to another, apart from his sin which he caused Judah
        to sin by doing evil in the eyes of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Manasseh and all that he did and his
        sin that he committed, are they not written on the scroll of the events of
        the days of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Amon Reigns in Judah Only Two Years'
      title: Amon Reigns in Judah Only Two Years
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Manasseh slept with his ancestors and was buried in the garden
        of his palace, in the garden of Uzza. Amon his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Amon was twenty-two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        two years in Jerusalem. The name of his mother was Meshullemeth the daughter
        of Haruz from Jotbah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh as Manasseh his father had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He walked in all of the way which his father had walked, and he served
        the idols which his father had served and bowed down to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He abandoned Yahweh the God of his ancestors and did not walk in
        the way of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The servants of Amon conspired against him and killed the king in
        his palace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But the people of the land killed all who conspired against the king
        and made Josiah his son king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Amon that he did, are they not written
        on the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'They buried him in his tomb in the garden of Uzza, and Josiah his
        son became king in place of him. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Josiah Becomes King in Judah'
      title: Josiah Becomes King in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'Josiah was eight years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        thirty-one years in Jerusalem. The name of his mother was Jedidah the daughter
        of Adaiah from Bozkath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did right in the eyes of Yahweh, and he walked in all of the way
        of David his ancestor and did not turn aside to the right or to the left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It happened in the eighteenth year of King Josiah, the king sent
        word to Shaphan the son of Azaliah the son of Meshullam, the secretary of
        the temple of Yahweh, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CGo up to Hilkiah the high priest, and let them count the money
        being brought to the temple of Yahweh which the keepers of the threshold
        have collected from the people, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and let them give it into the hand of those appointed doers of the
        work at the temple of Yahweh. Let them give it to the doers of the work who
        are at the temple of Yahweh to repair the breach of the temple: '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'to the skilled craftsmen, to the builders, to the masons, and to
        buy timber and hewing stones to repair the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: A Scroll of the Torah Discovered in the Temple'
      title: A Scroll of the Torah Discovered in the Temple
      number: 7
      content: "Only the money being given to them is not to be accounted for by
        them, for they are dealing with honesty.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Hilkiah the high priest said to Shaphan the secretary, \u201CI
        have found the scroll of the Torah in the temple of Yahweh,\u201D and Hilkiah
        gave the scroll to Shaphan and he read it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Shaphan the secretary came to the king and returned the king a word,
        and he said, \u201CYour servant poured out the money found in the temple,
        and they have given it into the hand of the doers of the work appointed over
        the temple of Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Shaphan the secretary informed the king saying, \u201CHilkiah
        the priest has given me a scroll.\u201D Then Shaphan read before the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When the king heard the words of the scroll of the Torah, he tore
        his clothes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the king commanded Hilkiah the priest, Ahikam the son of Shaphan,
        Acbor the son of Micaiah, Shaphan the secretary, and Asaiah the servant of
        the king, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Prophetess Huldah Predicts Doom for Judah'
      title: The Prophetess Huldah Predicts Doom for Judah
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CGo, inquire of Yahweh for me and for the people and for all
        of Judah concerning the words of this scroll that was found. For the wrath
        of Yahweh that is kindled against us is great because our ancestors did not
        listen to the words of this scroll to do according to all that is written
        concerning us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Hilkiah the priest, Ahikam, Acbor, Shaphan, and Asaiah went to
        Huldah the prophetess, the wife of Shallum the son of Tikvah the son of Harhas,
        the keeper of the robes. Now she was living in Jerusalem in the second district.
        Then they spoke to her, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and she said to them, \u201CThus says Yahweh the God of Israel, \u2018Say
        to the man who sent you to me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh, \u2018Look I am bringing evil to this place
        and upon its inhabitants, according to all of the words of that scroll that
        the king of Judah has read "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "because they have abandoned me and they have burned incense to other
        gods, provoking me to anger with all of the works of their hands. My wrath
        shall be kindled against this place and not be quenched.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And to the king of Judah who sent all of you to inquire of Yahweh,
        thus you shall say to him, \u201CThus says Yahweh the God of Israel, \u2018Concerning
        the words that you have heard, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'because you have a responsive heart, and you humbled yourself before
        Yahweh when you heard how I spoke against this place and against its inhabitants
        to become a desolation and a curse, and you have torn your clothes and wept
        before my face, I have also heard, declares Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Therefore look, I am gathering you to your ancestors, and you shall
        be gathered to your tombs in peace. Your eyes will not see all of the disaster
        that I am bringing onto this place.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D
        Then they reported the word to the king. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Josiah\u2019s Covenantal Reforms"
      title: "Josiah\u2019s Covenantal Reforms"
      number: 1
      content: 'So the king sent word, and all of the elders of Judah and Jerusalem
        gathered to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the king went up to the temple of Yahweh, and all of the men
        of Judah and all of the inhabitants of Jerusalem were with him, including
        the priests, the prophets, and all of the people from smallest to greatest;
        and in their hearing he read all of the words of the scroll of the covenant
        that had been found in the temple of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the king stood by the pillar, and he made a covenant before
        Yahweh, to go after Yahweh and to keep his commands and his warnings and
        his statutes, with all of his heart and with his all of his soul, to keep
        the words of this covenant written on this scroll. Then all of the people
        joined in the covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the king commanded Hilkiah the high priest, the second priests,
        and the keepers of the threshold, to bring out of the temple of Yahweh all
        of the objects made for Baal and for the Asherah and for all the host of
        heaven, and he burned them outside of Jerusalem in the fields of the Kidron,
        and then he carried their ashes to Bethel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He removed the priests whom the kings of Judah had ordained to burn
        incense on the high places at the cities of Judah and around Jerusalem and
        who offered incense to, to the sun, to the moon, to the constellations, and
        to all the host of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He brought out the Asherah image from the temple of Yahweh outside
        of Jerusalem to the Wadi of the Kidron and burnt it there; then he pulverized
        it to dust and threw its dust upon the tombs of the children of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He tore down the shrines of the male shrine prostitutes which were
        in the temple of Yahweh, where the women were weaving shrines for the Asherah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he brought all of the priests from the cities of Judah and defiled
        the high places where the priests from Geba up to Beersheba burned incense.
        He tore down the high places of the gates which were at the entrance of the
        gate of Joshua, the governor of the city, which were on the left of each
        gate of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'However, the priests of the high places did not come up to the altar
        of Yahweh in Jerusalem, but they ate unleavened bread in the midst of their
        relatives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He defiled the Topheth which is in the Valley of Ben-Hinnom, to prevent
        anyone causing his sons or his daughters to pass through the fire for Molech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He kept the horses that the kings of Judah had dedicated to the sun
        from coming to the temple of Yawheh at the side room of Nathan-Melech the
        eunuch, which was in the court; and the chariots of the sun he burned with
        fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The altars which were on the roof of the upper room of Ahaz, which
        the kings of Judah had made, and the altars which Manasseh had made in the
        two courtyards of the temple of Yahweh, the king tore down and ran from there
        and threw their ashes into the Wadi Kidron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The high places which were east of Jerusalem, which were on the south
        of the Mountain of Destruction which Solomon king of Israel had built for
        Ashtoreth the abomination of the Sidonians and for Chemosh the abomination
        of Moab and for Molech the detestable thing of the Ammonites, the king defiled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He also broke into pieces the stone pillars and cut down the Asherah
        poles and covered their sites with human bones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Moreover, the altar which was in Bethel, the high place which Jeroboam
        the son of Nebat, who had caused Israel to sin, had built, even that altar
        and the high place, Josiah tore down. Then he burned down the high place
        and crushed the pole of Asherah worship to dust and burned it with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When Josiah turned and saw the tombs which were there on the hill,
        he sent and took the bones from the tombs and burned them on the altar. Thus
        he defiled them according to the word of Yahweh that the man of God had proclaimed
        who had proclaimed these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he said, \u201CWhat is this gravestone that I am seeing?\u201D
        The men of the city said to him, \u201CThis is the tomb of the man of God
        who came from Judah and proclaimed these things which you have done against
        the altar of Bethel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Josiah said, \u201CLet him rest and let no man move his bones.\u201D
        So they left his bones undisturbed with the bones of the prophet who had
        come from Samaria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Moreover, all of the shrines of the high places which were in the
        towns of Samaria which the kings of Israel had made to provoke Yahweh, Josiah
        removed, and he did to them like all of the deeds he had done in Bethel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Passover Renewed'
      title: Passover Renewed
      number: 20
      content: 'Then he slaughtered all of the priests of the high places who were
        there, on the altars, and he burned the bones of the humans on them. Then
        he returned to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the king commanded all of the people, saying, \u201CKeep the
        Passover to Yahweh your God, as has been written on the scroll of this covenant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For they had not kept this Passover from the days of the judges who
        had judged over Israel or during the days of the kings of Israel and the
        kings of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But in the eighteenth year of King Josiah, this Passover was kept
        for Yahweh in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Moreover, the mediums and the spiritists, the household gods and
        the idols, and all of the abominations that were seen in the land of Judah
        and in Jerusalem, Josiah removed in order to establish the words of the law
        written on the scroll that Hilkiah the priest had found in the temple of
        Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'There was not a king like him before him, who turned to Yahweh with
        all of his heart and with all of his soul and with all of his might according
        to the law of Moses, nor did one arise like him afterwards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'However, Yahweh did not turn from the fierceness of his great anger
        which was kindled against Judah because of all of the provocations with which
        Manasseh had provoked him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Yahweh had said, \u201CEven Judah I will remove from my face, as
        I have removed Israel; I will reject this city that I have chosen, even Jerusalem
        and the house of which I said, \u2018My name shall be there\u2019!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Josiah and all that he did, are they
        not written on the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'In his days, Pharaoh Neco, king of Egypt, went up against the king
        of Assyria at the Euphrates River. King Josiah went to meet him, and he killed
        him at Megiddo as soon as he saw him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Jehoahaz Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jehoahaz Reigns in Judah
      number: 30
      content: 'So his servants drove him dead in a chariot from Megiddo, and they
        brought him to Jerusalem and buried him in his tomb. Then the people of the
        land took Jehoahaz the son of Josiah and anointed him and made him king in
        place of his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Jehoahaz was twenty-three years old when he became king, and he reigned
        three months in Jerusalem. The name of his mother was Hamutal the daughter
        of Jeremiah from Libnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh according to all his ancestors
        had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Jehoiakim Replaces Jehoahaz'
      title: Jehoiakim Replaces Jehoahaz
      number: 33
      content: 'Then Pharaoh Neco confined him at Riblah in the land of Hamath, from
        reigning in Jerusalem, and imposed a levy on the land of a hundred talents
        of silver and a talent of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Pharaoh Neco made Eliakim the son of Josiah king in place of
        Josiah his father, and he changed his name to Jehoiakim. Then he took Jehoahaz
        and brought him to Egypt, and he died there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The silver and the gold Jehoiakim gave to Pharaoh; however, he taxed
        the land to give the silver to meet the demands of Pharaoh. Each according
        to assessment, he exacted payment of the silver and the gold from the people
        of the land to give to Pharaoh Neco. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        eleven years in Jerusalem. The name of his mother was Zebudah, the daughter
        of Pedaiah from Rumah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh according to all that his ancestors
        had done. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: First Invasion of Nebuchadnezzar; Jehoiakim Submits'
      title: First Invasion of Nebuchadnezzar; Jehoiakim Submits
      number: 1
      content: 'In his days, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up because Jehoiakim
        had become his servant for three years; then he turned and rebelled against
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Yahweh sent against him raiding bands of Chaldeans, raiding bands
        of Aram, raiding bands of Moab, and raiding bands of the Ammonites. He had
        sent them against Judah to destroy it, according to the word of Yahweh that
        he had spoken by the hand of his servants the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Surely, it was on the command of Yahweh against Judah to remove them
        from his sight because of the sins of Manasseh, according to all that he
        had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Also, for the blood of the innocent that he had shed\u2014and he
        filled Jerusalem with innocent blood\u2014Yahweh was not willing to forgive. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The remainder of the acts of Jehoiakim and all that he did, are they
        not written on the scroll of the events of the days of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Jehoiakim slept with his ancestors, and Jehoiachin his son became
        king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Jehoichin Succeeds Jehoiakim'
      title: Jehoichin Succeeds Jehoiakim
      number: 7
      content: 'The king of Egypt did not again come out from his land, for the king
        of Babylon had taken territory from the Wadi of Egypt to the Euphrates River. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Jehoiachin was eighteen years old when he began to reign, and he
        reigned three months in Jerusalem. The name of his mother was Nehushta daughter
        of Elnathan from Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Second Invasion of Nebuchadnezzar'
      title: Second Invasion of Nebuchadnezzar
      number: 9
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh according to all that his father
        had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'At that time, the servants of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came
        to Jerusalem, and the city came under the siege. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came against the city while his
        servants were besieging it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Jehoiachin king of Judah went out to the king of Babylon, he, his
        mother, his servants, his commanders, and his court officials. The king of
        Babylon took him in the eighth year of his reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then he took from there all of the treasures of the temple of Yahweh
        and the treasures of the palace of the king. He cut up all of the vessels
        of gold which Solomon the king of Israel had made in the temple of Yahweh,
        as Yahweh had foretold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He deported all of Jerusalem: all of the commanders, ten thousand
        of the skilled warriors, and the artisans; no one was left over except the
        poorest of the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He deported Jehoiachin to Babylon; the mother of the king, the wives
        of the king, his court officials, and the citizenry of the land he caused
        to go into exile from Jerusalem to Babylon: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'of all of the skilled men, seven thousand, and of the skilled craftsmen
        and the artisans, one thousand. All of the mighty warriors fit for war the
        king of Babylon brought captive to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Zedekiah Replaces Jehoiachin'
      title: Zedekiah Replaces Jehoiachin
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the king of Babylon made Mattaniah his uncle king in his place
        and changed his name to Zedekiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned
        eleven years in Jerusalem. The name of his mother was Hamutal daughter of
        Jeremiah from Libnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He did evil in the eyes of Yahweh just like all that Jehoiakim had
        done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For it happened because of the anger of Yahweh, in Jerusalem and
        in Judah, until they were cast out from his presence. Then Zedekiah rebelled
        against the king of Babylon. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Final Invasion of Nebuchadnezzar'
      title: The Final Invasion of Nebuchadnezzar
      number: 1
      content: 'It happened that in the ninth year of his reign, in the tenth month,
        on the tenth of the month, Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon came, he and
        his army, against Jerusalem. He encamped against it and built siege works
        against it all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the city came under siege until the eleventh year of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In the ninth month, the famine became severe in the city, and there
        was no food for the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the city was breached, and all of the men of war entered by
        night by way of the gate between the wall which was by the garden of the
        king, and the Chaldeans were against the city all around, so he left by the
        way of the Arabah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the army of the Chaldeans pursued the king, and they overtook
        him in the Arabah of Jericho, and all of his army scattered from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So they captured the king and brought him up to the king of Babylon
        at Riblah, and they passed sentence on him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Jerusalem Is Sacked and the Temple Burned'
      title: Jerusalem Is Sacked and the Temple Burned
      number: 7
      content: 'They slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes; then they
        blinded the eyes of Zedekiah and bound him in bronze fetters and brought
        him to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the fifth month, on the seventh of the month, that is, the nineteenth
        year of King Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, Nebuzaradan, a commander
        of the imperial guard, a servant of the king of Babylon, came to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He burned the temple of Yahweh, the palace of the king, and all of
        the houses of Jerusalem; every large house he burned with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He and all the army of the Chaldeans who were with the imperial guard
        tore down the wall of Jerusalem all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The remainder of the people left in the city, the deserters who had
        deserted to the king of Babylon, and the remainder of the multitude, Nebuzaradan
        the commander of the imperial guard deported. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Plunder Taken by the Chaldeans'
      title: Plunder Taken by the Chaldeans
      number: 12
      content: 'But the poor of the land the commander of the imperial guard left
        for the vineyards and for tilling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The bronze pillars which were in the temple of Yahweh, the water
        carts, and the bronze sea that was in the temple of Yahweh, the Chaldeans
        broke into pieces and carried their bronze to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The pots, the shovels, the snuffers, the dishes, and the vessels
        of bronze with which they served there, they took. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The firepans and the basins, whatever was gold, the commander of
        the imperial guard took for the gold and whatever was silver, for the silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The two pillars, the one sea, and the water cart which Solomon had
        made for the temple of Yahweh, there was no weighing to the bronze of all
        of these vessels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The height of the one pillar was eighteen cubits; a bronze capital
        was on it, with the height of the capital being three cubits. The latticework
        and pomegranates on the capital all around were bronze, and likewise on the
        latticework for the second pillar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the commander of the imperial guard took Seraiah the chief priest,
        Zephaniah the second priest, and three of the threshold keepers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "From the city he took one court official who was chief officer over
        the men of war, five men from the king\u2019s council who were found in the
        city, the secretary of the commander of the army who mustered the people
        of the land, and sixty men from the people of the land being found in the
        city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Nebuzaradan commander of the imperial guard took them and brought
        them to the king of Babylon at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Gedaliah Appointed Governor'
      title: Gedaliah Appointed Governor
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the king of Babylon struck them down and killed them at Riblah
        in the land of Hamath; thus Judah was removed from its land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now as far as the people left in Judah whom Nebuchadnezzar king of
        Babylon left behind, he appointed Gedaliah the son of Ahikam the son of Shaphan
        over them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When all of the commanders of the troops heard, they and the men,
        that the king of Babylon had appointed Gedaliah, they came to Gedaliah at
        Mizpah, even Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, Johanan the son of Kareah, Seriah
        the son of Tanhumeth the Netophathite, Jaazaniah the son of the Maacathite,
        they and their men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Gedaliah swore to them and to their men, and he said to them, \u201CYou
        must not be afraid because of the Chaldeans. Settle in the land and serve
        the king of Babylon, and may it go well with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But it happened in the seventh month that Ishmael the son of Nethaniah
        the son of Elishama from the offspring of the kingship came, and ten men
        with him, and they struck down Gedaliah so that he died with the Judeans
        and with the Chaldeans who were with him at Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Elderly Jehoiachin Cared for in Babylon'
      title: Elderly Jehoiachin Cared for in Babylon
      number: 26
      content: 'Then all the people, from youngest to oldest, and the commanders
        of the troops, went to Egypt, for they were afraid of the presence of the
        Chaldeans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'It happened in the thirty-seventh year of the exile of Jehoiachin
        king of Judah, in the twelfth month on the twenty-seventh of the month, lifted
        Evil-Merodach king of Babylon in the year that he became king, the head of
        Jehoiachin king of Judah from the house of imprisonment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He spoke kindly to him, and he gave him a better seat than the seat
        of the kings who were with him in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So he changed the clothes of his imprisonment, and he ate food continually
        in his presence all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'His allowance was continually given to him from the king, a portion
        every day all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
